Mega Joker Review.text: Mega Joker is a video slot coming from one of the biggest land based casino games suppliers, Novomatic. The game is a combination of a classic fruit slot and a modern video slot with the end result being a fun and exciting game.

Theme and Visual Details.text:
For this slot the designers decided to go with the immortal fruit theme. To spice things up they used state of the art animations and high symbol details to give the game an attractive appearance.
While you spin the reels in the background you will hear the recognizable Novomatic slot sound just like you would if you were playing in a real brick and mortar casino.

Gameplay.text: The gameplay in Mega Joker is very fast and exciting. The slot lacks a classic bonus round so the excitement on the reels comes only from the game symbols and the Joker. Each spin of the reels gives you a chance to land a full screen of matching symbols and a big payout.

media.caption: Video showing the only bonus feature of the game - Joker Wild symbol win

Bet size and payouts.text:
Mega Joker is a 40 winline slot with 5 reels and 4 rows of symbols. Players are able to bet anywhere from $0.40 up to $200 per spin.
The top payout in the game comes from landing 5 scattered Stars on the reels, awarding the player with a 500 times the total stake payout. But if you’re lucky enough to land a full screen of Jokers you will win the jackpot prize of 2,000 times the total stake.
The slot comes with an RTP value of 95.05% and a medium variance.

media.caption: Paytable of Mega Joker slot

Bonus features.text:
As we mentioned earlier Mega Joker doesn’t have a classic bonus round. The only feature in the game comes from the Wild Joker symbol. It can land on all reels and will substitute for all game symbols except the Scatter.
The best part about the Joker is that it can land stacked across the reels, so you can end up with a full screen of Wild Jokers. Each 5 of a kind win with the Joker symbol awards a 50 times the total stake payout, so landing a full screen of Jokers will award you the top 2,000 times the total stake payout.

media.caption: Stacked symbols in Mega Joker slot can add some nice winnings

Conclusion.text:
Mega Joker is an interesting and very popular slot across Novomatic casinos. Sure enough the game might not be as exciting like other Novomatic slots which which have free spins or some other bonus rounds, but the Wild Joker certainly makes up for this disadvantage.
The medium variance of the slot allows for some nice payouts to land frequently on the reels so your balance won’t sink too fast most of the time. All you need is one great spin and a full screen of Jokers in order to walk away with the top payout in the game.

overview:

about_game: Kitty Glitter is well made, but fails to impress. With an RTP of 94.92% players are unlikely to stick around for the profits, though strategic players may be attracted to the high-variance offered by the bonus system in which an accumulator increases the number of wild symbols.

Theme and Story Line.text:
Kitty Glitter comes with no real story line and a straightforward theme.
As the title suggests the theme is cats: Siamese cats, Calicos and Tabbies with the top cat being the Persian. The ‘glitter’ is there largely in the Diamond symbols that work as wilds and scatters in the bonus rounds (more on which later).
The theme should appeal to anyone who agrees with the movie Homeward Bound – ‘cats rule, dogs drool’.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The adorable kitties in the symbol artwork are a little rough, and generally less enjoyable to look at than a cat should be. However they are easily read and well animated on the reels.
The sound design is also solid. Not great, but not making any major mistakes and with a nice spike when the Bonus symbol lands.
Overall it is more functional than beautiful.

media.caption: Kitty Glitter win

Kitty Glitter Gameplay.text:
The gameplay is pretty much what you’d expect. Five reels, 1 to 30 win lines and no additional frills. Hit spin and watch the cats go.
This simplicity does make for rather bland gameplay. Apart from the occasional bonus rounds, the gameplay does not vary much from spin to spin and there are no extra features like scatter, stacks or tumbling symbols.
Though for many players this would not be an issue, I would prefer a little more variation and if you feel the same way it might be worth looking at some of the other slots reviewed on our site.

media.caption: Kitty Glitter gameplay

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins in Kitty G.text:
The game comes with the standard additional symbols a Wild symbol (with ‘Kitty Glitter’ written on it) in and Bonus symbols (with an image of a cat food bowl full of diamonds). The Wild can play as any symbol with the important exception that is does not act as a Bonus symbol.
Bonus spins can be won by getting three Bonus symbols on the middle three reels. Each bonus round is fifteen free spins and the reels are more likely to hit during these spins due to increased wilds and bonuses.
Another fifteen spins can be retriggered during the bonus rounds by hitting three Bonus symbols on the middle reels again.
To make the bonus spins even more profitable, the Bonus symbol then becomes wild in the Bonus rounds, and each time one appears on reel 5 it is added to an accumulator that makes more symbols wild on certain reels.
For example three diamonds in the accumulator makes the White Persian Cat symbol wild on reels 2 to 5. This is where the big wins happen.

Kitty Glitter Bet Sizes, RTP and Varianc.text: The game has a medium to high variance, which we normally like, but the RTP is rather low, at 94.92%. The site we tried had coin sizes ranging from £0.01 up to £5.00 allowing for you to bet from £0.01 up to £150 on each spin.

media.caption: Kitty Glitter paytable

Conclusion.text:
Kitty Glitter is an unexceptional, but basically well made slot machine. It suffers from a slightly low RTP.
The bonus system works nicely, but hits very rarely making for a high-variance experience.
Though not much to look at it is well animated and plays smoothly. Dog lovers need not apply!

As expected the visual details in the slot are on a low level, while there are hardly any modern animations on the reels. Still this is a classic slot and the designers paid more attention to the payout potential of the game, rather than focusing on the visual appearance.

Gameplay.text:
Triple Diamond has a simple design with 3 reels and 3 rows. The designers installed 9 paylines in the game, leaving the player with more chances to win than on most classic slots where the number of paylines usually varies from 1 to 5.
The paytable in Triple Diamond consists of Single, Double and Triple Bars symbols, along with the Sevens symbol and the Wild.
The biggest excitement and payouts in the slot can land with a little help from the Wild symbol. When one Wild substitutes another symbol in a winning combination the overall payout is multiplied by 3. When two Wilds substitute in a win the payout comes with a high 9x multiplier. This way the payouts from the regular game symbols are much higher, thanks to the attached Wild multipliers.

media.caption: Triple Diamond offers more paylines than its predecessor, Double Diamond slot
Video featuring a win with Wild symbol, which multiplies the win

Bet size and payouts.text:
The bet size in Triple Diamond can vary from one casino to another. Depending on the casino the stake can go from $0.09 up to a whopping $900 per spin. It is easily adjusted by setting the Line bet anywhere from 0.01 to 100. The Auto Play function offers up to 50 Auto Spins.
Winning combinations in the game are formed by landing 3 matching symbols on a payline. The biggest payout in the slot comes from landing 3 Wilds on a winning payline. After that comes the Sevens symbol, followed by the Single, Double and Triple Bars symbols.
But what can keep your balance from dropping too fast are the few lower payouts in the game. Any one Wild on the reels will award a 2 times the total stake payout, any two Wilds will award a 10 times the total stake payout, while any Bars combination will pay 5 times the total stake.
The RTP value in Triple Diamonds is set at 95.06%. Compared to modern video slots this is a below average value, but compared to most classic slots the RTP is a bit higher. The slot has a low to medium volatility, so you can expect frequent wins to keep your balance from sinking too fast.

media.caption: Triple Diamond paytable

Conclusion.text:
Triple Diamond is sure to catch the attention of all players who enjoy spinning the reels of classic slots.
The paytable in the game is strong and the payout potential is enhanced by the multipliers attached to the Wild symbols. This way the top payouts in the slot can be multiplied by 9, so landing a 3 of a kind win with two Wilds and a Seven will result in a payout of 900 times the total stake.
With a top payout of 1,119 times the total stake and an RTP value of 95.06% Triple Diamond is a slot well worth playing.

about_game: Aloha! Cluster Pays is a great slot from NetEnt with a colorful Hawaiian theme and two interesting game features that make the game thrilling to play. The payouts are based on clusters of symbols appearing on the game’s six reels with five symbols each. Read the game’s review and try it out before playing for real money.

Aloha! Cluster Pays Review.text: Aloha! Cluster Pays (or simply just Aloha) is a popular slot machine created by NetEnt. Unlike the majority of slot machines, Aloha doesn’t have classic winlines. The wins depend on how many of the same symbols are clustered together instead. This game mechanics, combined with two interesting special features and colorful imagery, makes playing the Aloha slot machine a very enjoyable experience.

Theme, graphics and animations.text:
Everybody should be able to guess the theme of this game just by looking at its name. Yes, it’s related to Hawaii and Hawaiian culture. Almost all of the symbols (with the exception of the wild symbol) have something to do with Hawaii, ranging from flowers, pineapples, coconuts and shells all the way to colorful totems – the highest paying symbols in the game.
The game’s graphics and sounds stay true to its theme. Bright colors, smooth animations and great choice of music and sound effects really make Aloha! Cluster Pays a fun video slot game to play.

media.caption: Base game win in the Aloha! Cluster slot machine

Aloha! Cluster Pays gameplay and special.text:
Aloha! Cluster Pays features six reels with five symbols each, but there are no winlines. Winning combinations are created by creating clusters of the same symbols on the reels, with the minimum number of symbols needed to win something being nine.
The Aloha slot machine wouldn’t be the same and nearly as enjoyable without its two special features:

media.caption: Mega big win in the Aloha! Cluster slot

Sticky Win Re-Spins.text:
Sticky Win Re-Spins is a feature you will encounter quite often when playing Aloha! Cluster Pays. It can be randomly triggered after creating any winning combination.
This feature locks in the winning symbols and spins the rest of the reels again. If new symbols are added to the winning combination, it happens again. This keeps happening until no new symbols are added to the winning combination during a re-spin, which marks the end of the feature and the game round itself.
Take a look at the video below to see what the Sticky Win Re-Spins feature looks like in the game itself.

media.caption: Aloha! Cluster Pays Sticky Win Re-Spins feature

Aloha! Cluster Pays Free Spins.text:
To launch free spins, you must get at least three Free Spins symbols anywhere on the reels. You get nine free spins for three of these symbols, as well as one more for each additional symbol, all the way up to 12 free spins for six Free Spins symbol.
The free spins in Aloha can be retriggered (1 spin for 3 symbols, 2 spins for 4 symbols, 3 spins for 5 symbols, 4 spins for 6 symbols). You are only awarded a small number of additional spins, but those are extremely valuable, because of a special characteristic of the free spins feature.
The Free Spins feature in Aloha! Cluster Pays doesn’t just give you a certain number of free spins. First couple of spins are just like the spins during the regular gameplay, but then things start getting more interesting:
So, there are only the premium totem symbols left on the reels after eight spins, which is precisely why the few extra spins you can earn thanks to retriggers can be extremely valuable. Without the worse-paying symbols "blocking the way", the premium symbols can form big clusters that can award you with really nice wins.
And one more thing… The game designers at NetEnt probably didn’t want the players to exit the Free Spin feature with a frown on their faces, which might be why they decided to include one extra feature. If your last free spin ends up without a win, you’ll get one more spin. This keeps happening until you actually hit something, but it shouldn’t take too long. With only three types of symbols remaining on the reels, you usually hit at least something in the last spin.

Aloha! Cluster Pays RTP and volatility.text:
The RTP of this video slot is 96.42%, which makes it a rather average game in terms of the payout ratio, or possibly a bit better than the average which is somewhere around the 96% mark according to most sources.
When it comes to the frequency of winning spins and the sizes of individual spins, I consider Aloha! Cluster Pays to have a low to medium volatility (variance). Although the game can hit quite big, the individual wins generally stay smaller and only get really big thanks to the Aloha’s special features.

media.caption: Full paytable of the Aloha! Cluster slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Aloha! Cluster Pays is another great NetEnt video slot game, which is mostly popular for its great graphics, animations, music and the overall feel, at least in my opinion. That being said, the game’s special features make Aloha really thrilling and enjoyable to play. The Free Spin feature has a great special element to it, thanks to which you always win at least something after triggering it.

title: Gonzo's Quest
overview:
Gonzo's Quest
    
        Play Gonzo's Quest demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Gonzo’s Quest is an especially well-designed slot game created by one of the most popular game providers, Swedish company NetEnt, which describes it as “its first platinum video slot game".

Gonzo’s Quest review.text:
Gonzo’s Quest is an especially well-designed slot game created by one of the most popular game providers, Swedish company NetEnt, which describes it as "its first platinum video slot game". The game is beautiful to look at, has nice and swift animations and allows its players to win big, especially after triggering the Free Falls feature with increasing win multiplier.
Those are just some of the reasons why Gonzo’s Quest became popular right after its launch in 2010 and still remains a go-to game for many players to this date.
Read my Gonzo’s Quest review and find out everything there is to know about this game, including:

Gonzo’s Quest theme and story line.text:
Gonzo’s Quest follows the story of Gonzo the conquistador in the year of 1541. This explorer arrives to the Peruvian coast on a galleon and decides to abandon his ship and begin his search for Eldorado, the lost city of gold. He steals a treasure map, jumps off the ship and begins his journey. All of that is displayed in the game’s intro.
When the intro reaches its end, Gonzo poses beside the game's reels, becoming a constant feature of Gonzo’s Quest. He doesn’t change the outcomes of the spins, but stands there and celebrates with you when you hit a nice win.
The theme of the game is based around the culture of Incas, which is famed for its unique architecture and art. The architecture forms the game’s background, while the famous Inca masks take a form of the symbols, accompanied by likenesses of wild animals created in a similar style. All in all, Gonzo’s Quest offers a really unique experience.

media.caption: A cinematic introduction to Gonzo's Quest

Gonzo’s Quest graphics, sounds and anima.text:
Great graphics and smooth animations definitely are among the reasons that make Gonzo’s Quest so popular. The gameplay is swift and fast, which only increases the thrill of playing this game. You can enjoy the sounds of blocks falling onto the reels, while hoping for them to form a new winning combination to trigger another avalanche.
However, there is one complaint that many players share. The animations are a bit too fast when using the Autoplay feature. Many players like to look at new symbols falling onto the reels and figure out what exactly they need to form another winning combination. That’s almost impossible to do when using Autoplay, which is a shame, as it decreases the amount of fun some players have when playing Gonzo’s Quest.
Gonzo’s Quest simply is a beautiful game with a great mix of animations, 3D effects and sounds that make playing it a very enjoyable experience, which can also be said about many other NetEnt games.

media.caption: A demonstration of Autoplay animation speed of Gonzo's Quest

Gonzo’s Quest gameplay.text:
Gonzo’s Quest really distinguished itself among other slots with the way the game works. Instead of classic reels, the game has a so-called Avalanche feature, which has symbols fall into the reels from the top. Symbols that form a winning combination get destroyed and make room for new blocks of symbols to fall in from the top.
Thanks to the Avalanche feature, numerous consecutive wins can be achieved in the same game round. What’s more, every time new symbols are added to the reels, the multiplier increases. Each spin starts with a 1x multiplier (with the exception of free spins). Then it can increase with consecutive wins in the same game round to 2x, 3x and subsequently 5x, which is the maximum multiplier that can be achieved outside of the free spins feature.
There are 5 "reels" with 3 symbols each and the number of winlines is 20. You can’t choose the number of active winlines, it always remains "locked" at 20. This makes Gonzo’s Quest not suitable for some of my slot machine strategies, but it makes sense, as the Avalanche feature, which is one of the cornerstones of this game, wouldn’t work very well with fewer winlines. Winning combinations must appear on a winline from leftmost to right.
There are 7 regular symbols in the game. They are a bit difficult to describe because of the abstract nature of the game, so I will include a picture with them. Apart from the 7 regular symbols, there is a Free Fall symbol and a Wild symbol. Three Free Fall symbols in a winline triggers 10 free spins (or Free Falls as they are called in Gonzo’s Quest). The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols, including the Free Fall symbols.
The Avalanche feature really is what made this game so popular. It’s the core component of Gonzo’s Quest’s gameplay that makes the game much more interesting and thrilling to play. It can be really exciting to hit multiple consecutive wins in a single game round, just to see the multiplier rise and root for another big win with the combination of old symbols and the ones that have newly fallen onto the reels.

Gonzo’s Quest free spins – Free Falls.text:
Gonzo’s Quest has only one special feature, the Free Falls. Three Free Fall symbols trigger 10 Free Falls (free spins). However, the Free Fall symbols don’t function as scatter symbols, therefore they have form a winline from leftmost to right.
That makes the Free Falls much harder to hit, but at the same time it creates a possibility to trigger much more Free Falls at once. Each winline with three Free Fall symbols triggers 10 Free Falls, so you can be awarded with much more free spins if you manage to align them on multiple winlines.
What makes the Free Falls special, are the increased multipliers. Regular game starts at 1x multiplier that can subsequently rise to 2x, 3x or to the maximum of 5x. In the Free Falls, all of these multipliers are 3-times higher. That means that each Free Falls starts at 3x and can rise to 6x, 9x and 15x. This means you can really achieve nice winnings during the Free Falls.
The Free Falls feature is really interesting for the player, both from the perspective of unique experience and the possibility to hit a big win. However, it can be quite hard to hit, as the Free Fall symbols must form a winning combination on a winline, just like any other symbols.
That’s my main criticism of Gonzo’s Quest. It only has one special feature, which is not triggered very often. It doesn’t have any other bonus feature or a jackpot. That can make the gameplay a bit boring for some players, especially after playing some of the newer games with multiple special features that can be triggered in any spin.

media.caption: A generous Free Falls win some player captured on video

Gonzo’s Quest bet and win sizes.text:
Gonzo’s Quest has a minimum bet of €/£/$0.2 (€/£/$0.01 per winline) and a maximum bet of €/£/$50 (€/£/$2.5 per winline). Of course, the maximum and minimum bets be different in casinos with other currencies. You control the size of your bet using the "Coin value" and "Bet level" buttons.
All of the wins in the paytable are displayed in multiples of bet per line. The highest possible win per line awards 2,500x the bet per line, which is $25 for the minimum bet of $0.2 and $6,250 for the maximum bet of $50. That’s 125x the total bet, which is not so high when compared to some other slots, but you have to keep in mind the possible multiplier.
The maximum multiplier is 5x in regular gameplay and 15x during Free Falls. That means the highest win per line is 625x the total bet in regular gameplay (with the 5x multiplier) and 1,875x during Free Falls. The last number is really nice, as it means a possible win per line of $93,750 when betting $50 and $375 when betting $0.2.
On top of that, you have to keep in mind there always are 20 active winlines and you have multiple chances of winning in one game round, thanks to the Avalanche feature. Of course, huge wins like the ones I mentioned are incredibly rare, as basically in any other video slot game.

Gonzo’s Quest RTP and variance.text:
Gonzo’s Quest RTP (return to player) is 96 %. That means that you can expect to "win" $0.96 for every $1 you wager. Of course, this value only works statistically and in the long run, so your results will vary.
The RTP of 96 % can be considered somewhat of an average in the world of online slots. That means that there are games which are worse for the player in the long run, but there are also many slot games that are much better in terms of RTP.
In terms of volatility (variance), Gonzo’s Quest can be considered a medium variance game. That means that the game generally awards medium-sized wins with medium frequency, at least when compared to other video slots. The concept of variance can be a bit difficult to grasp, so feel free to read the article I linked above.

Conclusion.text:
Gonzo’s Quest is a very entertaining and popular online slot with a strong position in video slots’ history. It was one of the first (if not the first) games of its kind thanks to the Avalanche feature. Its medium volatility makes sure you win something every once in a while, while you also have a reasonable chance to hit a big win, most often thanks to the Free Falls feature.
On the other hand, the RTP of 96 % means that there are games better for the player, however, this value can be considered an average and it’s nothing to frown upon. As I already mentioned, some players (including me) would welcome additional bonus features, as the game can become a bit boring after some time.

Jack Hammer review.text:
Jack Hammer is a slot machine from NetEnt which was also followed by sequels Jack Hammer 2 and Jack Hammer 3 thanks to its popularity. It features a comic book style and captures a fight between a superhero called Jack Hammer and The Evil Wüten.
It’s a fast-paced slot machine with some unique and interesting game elements, as well as action-packed spins and a free spins feature. Jack Hammer’s slick animations, unique graphic style and nice sound effects and background music make the game very enjoyable to play.

Jack Hammer gameplay.text:
After you first launch the game, Jack Hammer might seem just like any ordinary slot game with 5 reels, each with 3 reels. However, Jack Hammer works slightly differently. It’s true that symbols are organized in a 5x3 layout, but each of the symbols spins separately. It can be said that Jack Hammer has 15 individual reels. The number of active winlines is 25 and it can’t be changed.
What makes Jack Hammer even more interesting, is the Sticky win feature. When you first get a winning combination on at least one of the winlines, all reels that are not part of any winning combination spin again. If new symbols are added to the existing winning combinations, or if new ones are created, the non-winning reels spin again. This keeps happening until no new winning symbols are added or until all 15 reels (symbols) are used in at least one winning combination.

media.caption: Sticky win in the base game
Gameplay video featuring free spins

Jack Hammer free spins.text:
Apart from the Sticky win feature, there is also a feature of free spins. You win 10 free spins for 5 Free Spin scatter symbols. The number of awarded free spins increases with the number of Free Spin symbols, up to a maximum of 30 free spins for 9 or more symbols. All wins are tripled during the free spins. Triple wins and the Sticky win feature can result in very nice winnings from the free spins.
The Sticky win feature can also help you trigger the free spin feature. You need at least 5 Free Spin symbols, but if you get at least 3 at first, the other reels will spin again to give you a better chance to trigger free spins.

Jack Hammer RTP, volatility and bet size.text:
The Jack Hammer slot game has a very interesting RTP of 97 %, which is higher than the average RTP of slot machines. The bets start at €/£/$0.25 and can go as high as €/£/$125 per spin. The maximum win from one spin is 250 000 coins, with a bet of 10 coins per line and a full screen of the highest paying symbol – Jack Hammer. In other words, the maximum win per spin is 1000-times the total bet.
I consider Jack Hammer a game with medium volatility. The Sticky win feature can bring you quite nice wins, but the premium symbols are quite rare, so it can be tough to hit a substantial win in one spin. The free spin feature with a 3x multiplier can help, but it’s not a guarantee of a big win, as you can easily go 10 free spins without a single winning combination.

media.caption: Base game paytable for the Jack Hammer slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Jack Hammer’s smooth gameplay and a 97 % RTP make it a very interesting slot game to play. The Sticky win feature makes spins more thrilling, especially when you get an initial winning combination and root for good symbols to fill up the empty reels and increase your winnings.

Mega Fortune jackpots and bonus game.text:
Three Bonus symbols trigger a bonus game, during which you get a chance to win one of the game’s three jackpots or a smaller prize. The Bonus symbols, however, need to appear on an active winline and from leftmost to right. It doesn’t function as a scatter.

Mega Fortune free spins.text:
The other feature of the Mega Fortune video slot are free spins, which are launched whenever three or more Scatter symbols appear anywhere on the reels. When it happens, you choose one of them to reveal the number of your free spins and your multiplier.
If two or more Scatter symbols appear on the reels during the free spins themselves, you choose one of them, which either gives you more free spins or increases your multiplier. The maximum multiplier you can get is 5x, which is enough to bring you some really nice hits.

title: Balloonies
overview:
Balloonies
    
        Play Balloonies demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Balloonies is the oddest of all things: a gambling game with a front end that looks designed for children. Enough said.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Set in a frankly bizarre world of balloon animals, Balloonies comes off as if it had been designed for small children. Odd in an industry with a slashed-eighteen symbol on every webpage.
The symbols on every reel are soft edged images of cute animals made from balloons, on a background of bluest sky. This gimmick is mirrored by having the symbols float up from the bottom of the screen rather than drop down from the top as with most slots.
This childish theme has very little additional substance. No characters or setting to contextualise anything. The theme is little more than an excuse for a set of uninteresting visuals.

media.caption: Win in the base game

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Balloonies graphics do nothing to elevate the already rather limited sense of atmosphere. The entire slot is decked out in pastel coloured images. These are a small set of balloon animals before the designers give up and revert to the usual ace to ten designs for the rest of the symbols.
The animations that acompany them are barely enough to sell the floating balloon concept, let alone make it interesting. The soundtrack is a tired musical loop with reel sounds that are dull but thematically appropriate. For example, winning combinations disappear with the sound of a balloon popping.
All in all, this slot has a front end that feels tacky but has at least been thought through by the artists.

Gameplay.text:
Balloonies is a simple five by three slot machine with twenty win lines. It comes with a minor quirk on its Scatter symbols and a bog-standard free spin bonus.
No effort was spent in making this slot do anything that might elevate the gameplay.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
Balloonies comes kitted out with several special symbols. The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Bonus and Star symbol.
The Star Symbol serves as a scatter, paying out two times the player’s bet per line for every star that lands on a reel, regardless of location or order.
The Bonus Symbol is a more typical kind of Scatter; hitting three Bonus Symbols will pay out twice the player's total bet per spin, and will trigger a basic free spin bonus.
The Free Spin Bonus begins by having the player choose from three balloons, which will randomly assign between four and fourteen free spins. The Bonus cannot be retriggered, however, it is played on reels with an increased frequency of Star symbols.

media.caption: Big win from the free spins

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.23%. Our yardstick for average is roughly 96%, making Balloonies a marginally above average slot in this regard. Pretty much only in this regard.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€20.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is at the low end of medium, which makes it a poor match for our preferred slot machine strategies and more or less precludes a recommendation from us.

media.caption: Full paytable forr Balloonies slot

Conclusion.text:
Balloonies is a poor slot to look at and very mediocre to play. The RTP is acceptable, but the volatility is not high enough to tempt us.
We would recommend finding a different game.

title: Cleopatra Plus
overview:
Cleopatra Plus
    
        Play Cleopatra Plus demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Cleopatra Plus is a great slot let down by its RTP. Attractive as the design, gameplay, and volatility are, the vig is just too high to make it worth the rope.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Cleopatra Plus is one of a myriad of follow ons from classic brick and mortar slot machine Cleopatra. After it got a digital revamp the Cleopatra line has gone through a slew of versions culminating in Cleopatra Plus.
Cleopatra – the seductive beauty who seduced Julius Caesar, Mark Antony, and the imagination of artists ranging from Shakespeare to the coders at IGT – has a new gimmick this time around. She’s got levelling system based on the number of topless gentleman followers she accumulates on your playthrough.
Jump in and be enchanted by the world of Classical Egypt.

media.caption: Wilds are stacked on the reels

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Like many an IGT offerings Cleopatra Plus is a high-quality production. They clearly sank some money into the artwork and symbol design. The usual Kings, Queens, Knaves and Tens are given the King Tut treatment in gold and pearls.
The soundtrack also shows real production values, the kind of vaguely exotic middle eastern riff you’d expect from a game set in Egypt, with additional recordings of "Cleopatra" added for some sex appeal.
The animations are varied and smooth. There is very little wrong with the game from a visual standpoint.

Gameplay.text:
The basic gameplay is that of a standard five reel, forty payline slot. However there are a few interesting wrinkles when it comes to the bonuses.
There is a levelling system based on winning over "followers", with higher levels improving your RTP by unlocking more and better bonus options (each one identified with and area of the "bonus map") which are looked at in more detail below.
The gameplay is solid, and works well. However, given the rarity of hitting bonuses, it does become highly repetitive.
The only interesting choice is which lucky deity you chose. These symbols are spread out at first, but as you reach higher levels they stack for bigger wins when they do hit.

media.caption: Low symbols paytable
All Gods' symbols pay the same in Cleopatra Plus slot
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The specialised symbols in Cleopatra Plus include a wild Cleopatra Plus symbol which also multiplies your win by two if you win using it as a wild. It’s also the highest paying symbol if you manage a straightforward win with the symbol by lining a number of them up in a row.
Another nice feature is that the wild symbol often comes in stacks of 2 to 10 symbols.
The other special symbol is the Follower symbol. Every time one of these falls on any reel you get the number of followers on that symbol added to your running total. As you increase your number of followers your options for bonus get more and better.
The Follower symbol also serves to trigger the bonus if you manage to hit three of them on any three reels. The bonus game consists of placing the number of followers you trigger the bonus with on various sites on a "Bonus Map". These sites award you free spins, payouts and multipliers for the bonus spins round which follows.

media.caption: Collect the Follower symbols to level up your awards
Each God has it's own set of bonuses laid on a bonus map

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The RTP starts out as a dismal 92.89% and can only be improved by rising up through the levels. The highest RTP you can achieve is 96.50%. This is only reached if you manage to collect more than 1250 followers (which gets you to level 8) on one play-through.
If you stick with this poor payout to get the game up to the rather average 96.50% the game becomes a little more appealing thanks to its high-volatility. But getting that far is gonna be costly and a bit of a grind.
While you cannot vary the number of winlines, the number of coins you can bet per line ranges from 1 to 50. At the website we tested the coin values offered mean you could bet anywhere from $/£/€0.40 up to $/£/€2,000 per spin. Which more or less covers all bankroll sizes.

media.caption: Names of the Aset's follower levels

Conclusion.text:
Cleopatra Plus is a fun, well designed game that is highly attractive in almost every way.
Unfortunately the RTP of 92.89% is unacceptably low. And it requires you sinking too much time and money into the game to level up before that RTP becomes even close to playable.
A shame since in almost every other way it is a great slot.

title: Joker 81
overview:
Joker 81
    
        Play Joker 81 demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: A nice little slot in the vein of old fruit machines. Its high variance appeals, but without knowing its RTP (not available from the publisher) it is impossible to recommend.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Joker 81 carves out a classic, one-armed bandit, fruit machine style for itself. Its reels are adorned with the classic cherries, sevens, bars and watermelons of old style machines and a fruit salad of semi-new additions like plums and oranges.
The theme of old style no-fuss no-muss machines is also reflected in the creator’s choices for the gameplay. The 81 in the title refers to one of the simple bonus features (details below).

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are no fancier than they need to be. The background is dark with an abstract orange pattern, just enough for it not to feel like the field was left blank by the creators, but not enough to distract.
The symbols are well designed having that instant recognition that cartoony icons have, while not being too minimalist.
The sound design is almost non-existent. Just a simple clicking for the reels and bell sounds to indicate when the 81-line feature is triggered.

Gameplay.text:
Joker 81 is a four-reel slot machine with seven winlines and only one set of payouts. You have to hit four symbols on a pay line in order to win the prize.
There is a small variation on the standard gameplay described above. When the Bar (which also plays as a Wild) symbol falls on a reel it triggers the 81 winline feature. This adds 74 more lines to the reels for a total of 81 win lines.

media.caption: You can get some nice winnings when you hit fully stacked reels of the same symbol
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The only special feature for this slot is the 81 winline feature triggered by the Wild symbol. As well as triggering this feature the Wild symbol plays as any symbol and pays out 120 times your bet per spin if you hit four in a row on a winline.
If you like your games without too many frills and accessories this may well appeal to you.

media.caption: Full paytable of Joker 81 slot machine

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
Kajot Games do not provide an RTP for this game which is a concerning sign. While the industry average seems to be around 96% we can normally assume machines with a high return to player will make the effort to advertise this fact.
Since you have to hit four symbols to win a payout winnings come very rarely and tend to be pretty small unless you manage to hit a couple of stacked symbols with the Joker symbol. As a result, this game has a relatively high variance.
The range of bets available on the site we tested was €/£/$0.10 up to €/£/$100.00 per spin.

media.caption: Some nice big wins can be attained in Joker 81 slot machine even without info about its RTP

Conclusion.text:
Joker 81 is a nicely made, simple slot machine that evokes the simpler era of pull lever spin the reels type gameplay.
Even though we like its high variance, it is hard to recommend a slot that is so cagey with its other key statistic: its RTP.

about_game: Chase the end of the rainbow in Lucky Pot where the RTP is 98% and the gameplay simple but solid.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Leprechauns and the luck of the Irish is the craic for Lucky Pot, which sets itself beneath a rainbow in the famously verdant countryside of Ireland.
The green makes for a pleasant setting for a game, even if the pot of gold idea is largely done to death by the slot machine industry. As metaphors go, it is not particularly subtle.

media.caption: Win in the Lucky Pot slot

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are extremely well put together; but while they excel at the technical level, at the level of taste they leave a fair bit to be desired. The visuals are overly pastel in a way that feels cheap and lacking of weight.
On the other hand, the animations are put together with great care and the sound design is excellent. The musical soundtrack perfectly pastiches Irish folk music without becoming annoying and the slots have a pleasant heft to their spinning sounds.

Gameplay.text:
Lucky Pot is a four reel slot machine with three rows and 25 win lines.
The game has a few small details that liven up regular play. The one you will have most use of is a double or nothing gamble feature in which you can bet your winnings on the colour of the next lick of paint off a deck of cards. This is an excellent feature for upping the volatility of the game (more on which below).
If you happen to fill every reel with the same symbol, you not only win on all 25 win lines, but your winnings are doubled for that spin.

media.caption: Hit 3 Scatter symbols for a big win
Gameplay video featuring a Legendary win

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There is no Wild symbol in Lucky Pot.
There are no bonus features in Lucky Pot either. However, three or four Scatter symbols in one spin pay out a random multiple of your bet. The multiple will be between one and sixty-four if you hit three Scatters, and between four and one hundred and twenty eight for hitting four Scatters.

media.caption: Gamble feature in Lucky Pot game

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 98.00%. A really excellent return to player and well above average for the industry. Unfortunately, the volatility of this game is low to medium, meaning that you cannot take full advantage of the low vigorish with our preferred strategies.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum of $/£/€0.20 to a maximum bet per spin of $/£/€50.00. This is a pretty good range cutting out only the highest and lowest of rollers. Most mid-stakes players will be well covered here.

media.caption: Paytable for the Lucky Pot slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Lucky Pot is a deceptively high-quality game at the visual level, but under its shiny surface, the slot machine is actually a very simple one. Nevertheless, it is an interesting slot made by Synot Games.
There are no bonuses or Wilds. Instead, the game relies on solid fundamentals and a few twisty symbols in the base game to spice things up. This might be more effective in a game with higher volatility.
The return to player is the main draw with a vig of only 2% and a gamble feature that allows you to crank up the volatility to a level that is more appropriate for our preferred strategies.

overview:

about_game: Bullseye is a game show themed slot with a cartoon mascot and a fun look. It’s well built, with an alright RTP and great attention to detail. Give it a go and see if you can hit a bullseye to take down the jackpot.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Bullseye takes the form of 1960s TV game show in which a bull mascot offers up lifestyle changing prizes based on whether or not you, as the contestant, can hit the bullseye with a dart.
In practice, the way you win prizes is actually by matching symbols from reel to reel, but the conceit shows itself in the Bonus Games (more on this later) and in the choice of symbols: caravans, cars, holidays and cash, all classic prizes from TV shows like The Generation Game.

media.caption: Big win from free spins bonus feature

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are high quality, all drawn up in high definition and animated with shiny 3D animations for when you win. Overall the game looks lovely, though a little too much time was put into the bonus animations.
The background music is a piano theme tune from the imagined TV show and though fun to begin with, it grows old very fast. The rest of the sound effects are simple and go with the game show setting.

Gameplay.text:
The game is a five reel, 243-ways game. This means you can win simply by getting matching symbols on adjacent reels running left to right. This gives you many more ways to win than your average slot.
There are free spins and a bonus game to break up the repetitive pattern and the controls are clear and simple, allowing you to get straight into gaming as fast a possible.
All payouts are multiplied by your "Coin Bet" decided by the number of coins in the "Coin" section of the screen. This is different from the total number of coins bet per spin which is your coin bet multiplied by thirty.

media.caption: Multiple winlines hit
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There is a Wild symbol, a Bonus Symbol and a Scatter Symbol.
The Wild stands in for any symbols except the Bonus or Scatter.
Hit two or more Bonus symbols and you get to play the Bonus Board game. A pseudo darts game which is so slow to play it almost saps all the fun out of winning. Each stage of the game sits behind a good ten seconds of animation and there are a lot of stages. You pick five targets on a dart board and win a random prize from behind them.
The prizes behind each throw are between two and fifteen times your bet per spin.
The Bonus symbol also pays out if you land two or more on a win line paying out 50 times your "Coin Bet" (see above for details), up to 400 times for five symbols.
The Scatter pays out a multiple of your bet per spin (rather than your coin bet). x5 for three, x10 for four and x100 for five. When you win with the Scatter you also get 15 free spins during which all wins are doubled.

media.caption: Another bonus feature - Bully's prize board
Hitting free spins symbol in the bonus game - more free spins for you to enjoy

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The game has an RTP of 96.63% and has a medium to high level of variance.
This RTP is within our preferred range of +96% and the higher variance games play well with some of our recommended strategies.
The range of bet sizes are significant on this game with a min bet of $/£/€0.30, this might push out some players who are on a very small bankroll and looking to make sure they can stretch their game-time. The maximum bet on the site we tested was a massive $/£/€150.00 per spin.

media.caption: Low symbols paytable
High symbols paytable

Conclusion.text:
Bullseye is well made, pays out an acceptable amount, and works with our favoured strategies. Add to this the enjoyable (if rather slow) bonus game, and the additional free spins feature and you have a winner.
We recommend this to anyone with a bit of nostalgia for shows like The Price is Right.

overview:

about_game: The Carnaval online slot machine was released by Microgaming a few years back, with the intention to emphasize the colourful and entertaining motifs of the world-famous Rio de Janeiro Carnival.

Carnaval review.text:
The Carnaval online slot machine was released by Microgaming a few years back, with the intention to emphasize the colourful and entertaining motifs of the world-famous Rio de Janeiro Carnival.
This event, with its multi-layer meaning, starting from the fact it marks the period of Lent all the way to Easter through to its symbolism of the characteristic culture of the nation all the way down to its neighbourhoods, has been rightfully listed as one of the themes used in this reputable software company’s product offering.

Theme and Storyline.text:
As the name of the slot game already indicates, Carnaval is all about the theme of carnivals. With a particular focus on the Rio de Janeiro's carnival which has been noted through the use of some of its characteristic elements within the slot’s grid, Carnaval is bound to meet the needs of any player looking to have fun during their online slot gameplay.
The absence of a starting screen before the main slot grid appears does not mean that the slot isn’t intertwined with a storyline. In fact, it’s wildly indicative elements prompting players to travel to the vivid streets of Rio de Janeiro definitely set some backdrop other than the vibrant purple shade supporting the slot’s reels.

media.caption: Full paytable of Microgaming's Carnaval slot machine

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Each slot and casino game in Microgaming offerings has its own target audience in mind, and this particular title definitely aims to appeal to slot players interested in simpler gameplay. Even more so, the lack of particular bonus rewarding features may have contributed to such low-key animation effects.
Still, the slot’s graphic design and sound effects are fully compatible with the message it is trying to convey. The former is predominantly inspired by carnival props, instruments and even participants – such as the masked clown and dancer, while the soundtrack is not limited to the crowded sounds of the streets of Rio, but goes for a generally funkier overtone.

Gameplay.text: This 5-reel slot, featuring a selection of 9 paylines across its grid, despite its orientation to simple and straightforward gameplay, still manages to include a lot of fun and rewarding features. The slot is ultimately indicative of the theme when it comes to the symbols on the reels, having a generally rewarding effect. This is evident in the reel elements – symbols represented by trumpet, flag, clown and dancer, as well as the Carnaval logo itself.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Bonus features.text:
What has left some players disappointed has actually made others glad – this slot does not offer any extra game levels or bonus features as part of its classic, standard nature. Still, players that do like this type of titles and play on it are in for other benefits, triggered by the slot’s Wild and Scatter.
The Wild symbol has a feathery representation, while the Scatter symbol features some carnival-themed decorations.
The Wild symbol does not create any winnings on its own and is solely intended to perform the role of a substitute to all symbols, but the Scatter. Even though it can land on reels 2, 3 and 4 only, the Wild still has high reward potential.
As for the Scatter, it can land anywhere on the reels in order to trigger a win. Scatter wins multiply your total bet size with a max payout of 50x for landing five Scatters.

media.caption: Hit 3 Scatters and you win double your total bet

Bet size and payouts.text:
In terms of bet size, this slot allows players to stake from 1 to 9 coins per single spin, with a single coin value ranging from €/£/$0.25 to €/£/$100. Should players choose to pay and activate all 9 paylines, they would be staking the maximum bet size of €/£/$900, for a max win of 5,000 coins per single line.
Speaking of wins, the lowest value symbols are the cards commonly found on such, standard-designed slot reels, with the 10 and J paying 100 coins per payline, Q and K paying 120 coins and the A card paying 150 coins for 5 symbols. The trumpet’s max payout for 5 on a payline is 250 coins, the flag symbol pays 300, the white-faced clown pays 500, the dancer with the colourfull headdress – 600 coins, and the Carnaval logo symbol is the most rewarding – paying the aforementioned maximum of 5,000 coins for five on a payline.

RTP and Variance.text: The estimated RTP of the Carnaval title by Microgaming is 96.94%, which is an above average percentage. Such decent RTP, together with a medium variance offers some gameplay thrill.

Conclusion.text:
All in all, the Carnaval release by Microgaming is proof that slots don’t need to come packed with all kinds of features in order to obtain player’s interest.
If you are a player who doesn't require bunch of fancy bonus features, you're OK with an average RTP and medium volatility, then this Rio's Carnival themed slot might be just your kind of fun.

title: Candy Dreams
overview:

about_game: You might want to dream of something other than this medium volatility slot with an RTP of 96.82%.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Clouds of cotton candy, as starscape of hundreds and thousands, this is the dream Candy Dreams is selling.
Candy Dreams is set in a world that seems as much inspired by renaissance paintings of heaven as by the world of sweet treats. The colour scheme evokes associations with Candy Crush and other popular sugary games from outside the world of slots.
Whether this works for you is down to how sweet your tooth is.

media.caption: Big win in Candy Dreams slot

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are pretty middle of the road. They feel up to date, but don't stand out much, even in a world of frequently reskinned slot software.
The animations are unimpressive and despite their complexity fail to make reading the reels any easier, which is their main function.
The music is serviceable but low-fi, and the sound effects, like the animations, fail to enhance the player's experience.

Gameplay.text:
Visually Candy Dreams looks like it might be aiming to break the mould with its gameplay. The player is first struck by the reel format: 3-4-5-4-3. This look is deceiving, the main game is a basic click and win style slot.
The base game has no additional features, though there are two simple bonuses (details below) to spice things up.
Candy Dreams is an any way wins slot, where in place of win lines the slot pays out whenever three or more symbols appear anywhere on adjacent reels starting from reel one. This makes for 720 ways to win.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Planet and Lollipop symbols.
Three or more Planet symbols anywhere on the reels trigger a picking game, in which the player can win coins by picking planets and avoiding the Pop symbol which will end the game.
In addition to the winnings from the picking game, players also win a fixed amount depending on the number of Planet symbols that trigger the bonus game: 1x the bet per spin for three Planet symbols, 10x for four, and 100x for five.
The Lollipop symbol pays out the same amount but triggers a Free Spin bonus instead.

overview:

about_game: A bright and promising theme gives way almost immediately to a slot which lacks features, atmosphere, and volatility (low to medium). The RTP is barely average (96.07%) and is the best thing about it.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Crazy Chameleons creates a pantheon of kookie cartoon surfers who happen to be lizards. The multicoloured pals ride gnarly waves with boards as fancy as their swim-trunks.
Seagulls, sand, and blue horizons are the main symbols, with the crazy chameleons of the title being the highest paid symbol. It’s a fun ocean going setting with some real attitude.
Try not to catch the sun out there on the beach or you’ll end up changing colour too.

media.caption: Win in the Crazy Chameleons slot

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Crazy Chameleons has a rather old fashioned look about it. The artwork is cartoonish and pixely. Apart from the chameleon(s) there aren’t any other characters to spice things up. Instead, the graphics are made up of rather plodding beach scenery.
The age also shows in the simplistic animations. A line appears to show a win, but there is no movement to the slot apart from the spin animations.
Adding to the static feel of the slot is the lack of music. A dirty guitar sting kicks in after a win, but the main game is otherwise silent apart from some ocean sounds.

Gameplay.text:
Microgaming's Crazy Chameleons is a five reel, three row slot, with five win lines. The win lines pay out in both directions.
There are no bonus games, gamble features, or randomised features. The gameplay is very simple in a way that seems jarring when squared against the flamboyance of the theme.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols.
There are no bonuses or free spins though. This is unusual for a slot with so much character. Normally a minimalist play style goes with minimalist themes. But not here.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.07%, more or less exactly on our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€1.25 up to a maximum of $/£/€25.00 per spin. This is a rather high minimum spin, so low-rollers should probably keep on rolling.
The volatility of this game is at the low end of medium, which makes it a very poor match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Paytable for Crazy Chameleons slot machine

Conclusion.text:
The low volatility of this slot precludes it from getting a recommendation regardless of any other aspect of the slot.
But this one really doubles down. The gameplay is minimal, the bonuses non-existent. There are very few sound effects, less music, and one animation. The theme is barely fleshed out, there is just one character and it appears very rarely.
Everything about this slot feels lazy or unfinished. We do not recommend it.

title: Game of Thrones
overview:
Game of Thrones
    
        Play Game of Thrones demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Based on the hit TV series, this is a beautiful slot machine with some fun bonus and gambling features.

Theme and Story Line.text:
"In the Game of Thrones, you either win or you die," says Cersei Lannister early on in HBO’s hit TV show. The downside for losing at the Game of Throne slot machine is less severe. However, it is still a pretty tough game to beat.
Using the iconography created for the TV series, the Game of Thrones slot uses the warring of the major houses of Westeros as its central theme with the choice to pick a house during bonus rounds to affect your possible winning combos.
If you’re a fan of the TV show or books this might be the slot for you. If you can’t tell your Baratheons from your Lannisters, don’t worry, most of the characters can’t either.

media.caption: Game of Thrones - 2 scatter symbols random win

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Using the art created for the show this slot is pretty gorgeous to look at, with great attention paid to the details (even the font is classy).
Ramin Djawadi’s fantastic theme tune for the TV series plays on a loop as you go. If you do get tired of it, you can mute the music, but why would you?
The animations are nicely designed, especially the maps and coins in the gamble feature. And the reels are smooth and high definition.
All in all, it is one of the nicest looking slots we’ve played in a long time.

Gameplay.text:
The central gameplay is a standard five reel, 243 way win where symbols must appear in any location in neighbouring reels to win. The first symbol must be on the first reel.
To this is added a gambling feature that allows you to flip a coin up to four times playing double or nothing each time. Each time you win, you move further down the map. It should be noted that this will not affect your RTP, but the more you gamble the higher your variance.
There is also an opportunity to pick your bonus should you hit it (see below for the details of the bonus games).
These features add a nice variation to the pace of the game.

media.alt: Game of Thrones Choose Your Side
media.caption: Game of Thrones gamble feature - choose your side!

media.alt: Game of Thrones Gamble Feature Result
media.caption: Game of Thrones gamble feature - the result
Game of Thrones free spins gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Game of Thrones game has two special symbols in addition to the standard Ace to Jack and the four main houses: Targaryen, Stark, Lannister and Baratheon.
The first of these symbols is the Wild symbol. This has the Game of Thrones logo on and is stacked so when you hit with it you often hit multiple winlines at once.
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols, except for the Bonus symbol, which is an image of the Iron Throne. This has a couple of rules associated with it. First of all, it plays as a scatter symbol. If you hit just two, you receive a randomly determined cash prize. In our test play we've encountered a win of the bet amount or the bet multiplied by 2 or 3.
If you hit more than two bonus symbols, there is a payout on it as a scatter symbol and in addition to this, the bonus round is triggered. In the bonus round you are given the option of four different houses. You can choose fewer spins with a higher multiplier and a small stack of higher value symbols or you can get more free spins with a lower multiplier and larger stacks of lower value symbols.
Once you’ve picked your bonus the free spins begin. You can retrigger further spins during the bonus round allowing for some massive wins when they do arrive.

media.caption: Game of Thrones scatter symbols paytable

media.alt: Game of Thrones Free Spins Choice
media.caption: Game of Thrones free spins choice. Pick between the Houses: Baratheon, Lannister, Stark and Targaryen

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The bet sizes are surprisingly limited on this game with a choice of two coin sizes and between 1 and 10 coins.
Reports of the RTP vary from 95.01% to 95.5% which may be the result of the different choices of bonus.
The variance on this game is very high though, so expect long periods of watching your coins slowly deplete with the occasional big win.

media.alt: Game of Thrones Top Symbols Paytable
media.caption: Game of Thrones top symbols paytable

Conclusion.text:
This is a good looking slot machine from Microgaming with a fun gamble feature and an interesting choice mechanic for its bonus.
The RTP is a little below the industry average, but we like the high variance.
Overall it is an excellent gambling experience.

title: Kings of Cash
overview:
Kings of Cash
    
        Play Kings of Cash demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Solid, if unspectacular, gameplay, visuals and bonuses coupled with high volatility and an RTP of 96.60% make this one a winner.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Kings of Cash is another Games Global clone of a series with highly idiosyncratic naming conventions revolving around royalty and hard currency.
This one is as good as any other with the Kings of the title being the card from the deck brought to life and given thrones, crowns, and swag bags in the light-hearted cartoon imagery of the reels.
The theme is a bit thin as they go, the background is just a velvet hanging and the symbols are very limited in variety. That said, the overall tone of the game is not unappealing, but it is not going to entice everybody.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are in that Games Global sweet spot of being relatively flawless, but also completely lacking any excellence. There is little to criticise in the choice and design of images on the reels, but there’s also nothing about them to grab the attention of the player.
The animations are similarly basic, doing their job well, but with very little élan.
The spin and win sounds are perfectly fine as are the limited background tracks, but here too Kings of Cash has mustered just enough effort to not actively annoy its players.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Gameplay.text:
Kings of Cash is played on your bog-standard five reel layout, with three rows and fifteen winlines.
It comes with two types of bonus – a picking game and a free spin bonus (full details below) – which is a solid showing for a slot that isn’t pushing to be anything more than good at doing what everyone else is doing.

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the two types of Scatter symbols. There are no multipliers in this game for Wild symbol wins.
The two Scatter symbols are the Dollar symbol and Crown symbol. These symbols do not need to be on a winline for the player to win.
Three or more Dollar symbols anywhere on the reels trigger a cash payout and a free spin bonus. The more Dollar symbols over three the player hits, the bigger the cash payout and the more free spins the player is awarded.
Three Dollar symbols win one time the player’s bet plus ten free spins, while five Dollar symbols net ten times the bet and 25 free spins.
Three or more Crown symbols anywhere on the reels trigger a picking game in which twelve cards are dealt face down. Each card has a multiplier amount on it. The player is awarded a payout equal to their bet per spin multiplied by the number on the first three matching cards they turn over.

Its main appeal is not in its gameplay or visuals, but in its volatility and RTP. The high volatility and RTP of 96.60% makes this a good match for our slot machine strategy, and wins this slot our recommendation.

title: Mermaids Millions
overview:
Mermaids Millions
    
        Play Mermaids Millions demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Mermaids Millions is a nice little slot with an underwater theme. It is well designed and enjoys several bonus features to keep players interested. It is medium-volatility slot and has an RTP of 96.56%.

Theme and Story Line.text:
Mermaids Millions slot machine takes you down under the sea, where Neptune rules and the mermaids play. There is sunken pirates’ booty and all manner of sea creatures as well as the mythical mermaids who deliver the big bucks.
The theme clearly draws on Disney’s The Little Mermaid while making sure not to annoy Mickey Mouse’s copyright lawyers.
Like the lobster says: Everything’s better down where it’s wetter; take it from me.

media.caption: Mermaids Millions is a 5 reel slot with 15 winlines

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics and animations are professional and high def. They look excellent on any size screen. The fact that the background is blue can strain the eyes a bit, but the Symbols show up well against the colour and so the visuals do work.
The soundtrack between spins is a pleasant underwater bubbling noise, which is oddly relaxing. When you spin the reels the soundscape wakes up a bit and there are the chimes and spinning noises you would expect.
Overall Mermaids Millions looks good and sounds good.

Gameplay.text:
The basic game is a five reel slot with anywhere from one winline up to fifteen.
There are two different bonus games triggered by hitting either the Scatter or Treasure symbols (more on these below).
The slot is easy to get into and all the controls are highly intuitive. By switching on the expert settings you can set up the auto play options, or else use the preprogrammed 5x and 10x auto play buttons.
It all makes for a well-paced experience.

media.caption: Gameplay video featuring free spins

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
As previously mentioned the game has two bonus symbols: the Mermaid and Treasure symbols.
The Mermaid symbol is a Scatter. However, if you hit three or more of the Mermaid symbol you also trigger a Free Spin bonus of 10 free spins. During the free spins, every payout is tripled.
The Treasure symbol is a Bonus symbol. It triggers a minigame in which you may open a number of boxes to generate a prize. The more symbols you hit the bonus with, the more boxes you may open. You can still hit the treasure bonus during the Free Spins.
On top of this, the Neptune symbol is wild. This wild symbol will also pay out independently should you hit a winline with more than one of them.
The Neptune symbol can assist with hitting any winline apart from the Scatter (Mermaid) and Treasure symbols.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
This game has a decent RTP of 96.56% which is about the average for the industry.
There is a 75 coin maximum per spin. However, you can set the value of the coin from anywhere between $0.01 to €/£/$1.00 at the site we tested, which gives more than enough flexibility in your bet size (a bet spread of between €/£/$0.01 to €/£/$75.00 per spin).
Mermaids Millions is a medium volatility slot with a maximum single line payout of 7500 times the line bet (for five Neptune symbols) on a regular spin or 22,500 times during free spins.

Conclusion.text:
Mermaids Millions is nice to look at, with solid gameplay and a wide range of bonus features for such an old slot.
Its RTP is pretty standard so for our recommended strategies we would recommend increasing the volatility by playing fewer winlines.
All in all, it is a decent slot that is easy to recommend.

title: Doubles
overview:
Doubles
    
        Play Doubles demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Doubles is an old style fruit machine slot brought up to date and given a twist with its double symbols. The outrageous music and low volatility are small detractors from an otherwise very solid slot.

Theme and Story Line.text:
Doubles takes the classic one-armed bandit theme and adds a couple of twists to the theme.
Each symbol comes in both a single and double form. The double form counts as two for winline and payout purposes. The game also has a visual twist with the images being formed from old school looking polygon graphics.
Apart from that, the theme is pretty standard slot machine fare. Plenty of fruit, some lucky sevens, diamonds, and horseshoes.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are rather pleasing. The polygon cartoon style is bright and fun, the images easy to read off on each reel.
The spin noises are electronic thunks and chimes that are highly satisfying. Although the soundtrack music is a garish electronica beat that is very distracting. Luckily the game controls make turning the music off very easy.
The animations are very smooth, and the same settings that give you control over the music also allow you to adjust the speed of the animations so that you can either slow the game down to increase tension or speed it up to get as many spins into your session as possible.

media.caption: Small 5-symbols win

Gameplay.text:
The game is a five reel game with the 243 pay way system instead of standard winlines.
Each of the symbols comes in two types: single and double (indicated below by the difference between the double lemons and single lemons). Each double symbol counts as if you hit two of that symbol. So in the image below you win the value of hitting five lemons.
This means you can hit up to ten of any symbol by hitting one double on every reel (a double on every reel in that winline).
The downside of the gameplay is that bonus game is just free spins which can feel a little simplistic. Though it does introduce some interactivity which is always nice.

media.caption: Gameplay video featuring 10 free spins with top symbol pick, without luck though

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The bonus for this game comes in the form of free spins.
The Free Spin symbol triggers as a scatter symbol, so if you hit the Free Spin symbol on any three or more reels in any order you will win your free spins.
At the start of the free spins, you get to chose one symbol to double. For the duration of the free spins, the symbol you choose will have all the single symbols converted to doubles. The more valuable the symbol that you double is, the less likely you are to hit it. So although the choice doesn’t affect RTP, it will make a difference to your volatility.
Free spins are apportioned as follows: 3 Free Spin symbols get you 10 free spins, 4 gets you 20, and 5 symbols gets you 40 spins.
There is no wild symbol in this game.

media.caption: Choose your Doubles for the Free spins game

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
This is a low variance slot, which we tend to avoid for strategic reasons. It comes with a bog standard 96.00% RTP.
The possible bet size per spin range from €/£/$0.25 to €/£/$50.00 which is enough for most purposes, but might leave the highest and lowest rollers wanting to look elsewhere for their thrills.
These setbacks undermine an otherwise well put together slot.

media.caption: Highest possible win isn't very attractive for high rollers
Medium symbols paytable in the Doubles

Conclusion.text:
Doubles is a fun slot that is nice to look at and fun to play. It is a little over simple (one bonus of just free spins).
It is also somewhat let down by its low volatility although the RTP is a perfectly acceptable 96.00%.
This slot will appeal to those who like old school fruit machine slots.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Vikings Go Berzerk is set in the world of woad covered warriors and longship captains roving the North Sea and occasionally being set upon by vampire fanged mermaids known as sirens. After an opening cinematic in which statues of Vikings appear to be engaged in a pitched naval battle with these sirens, you begin the main game and are launched into the search for gold.
Like pirates and the California gold rush, Vikings are a natural place to go for a historical slot. They present plenty of opportunities for fun characters (there are four cartoonish Vikings in your crew) all of whom are as set upon gaining gold as you are.

media.caption: Vikings Go Berzerk slot has very high-def visuals

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Yggdrasil Gaming has taken the theme pretty literally. Apart from the sirens who only appear during free spins, you have your four crew members as symbols and coins in gold, silver, iron and copper.
These are all well drawn and come with varied 3D animations for their win states and separate berzerk animations (see below for details).
The music is a pleasant old fashioned orchestral score that does excellent justice to the setting.
Overall the design side of things is a real joy to look at, listen to and play with.

media.alt: Vikings Go Berzerk top symbol win
media.caption: Example of a simple win with the top symbol of the game

Gameplay.text:
The main game is a fairly straightforward twenty-five win line, five reel slot.
Most of the features in the game are best reviewed in the Wilds and Bonuses section below, but it is enough to say here that the features ensure the game doesn’t get dull. Unfortunately, they can be quite few and far between so the gameplay does rely heavily on the design aspects to prevent it from becoming too repetitive.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
These features though are a lot of fun.
The simplest bonus is the Treasure Chest symbols. The Treasure Chest provides five randomised gifts to the player of which the player can choose one to keep. It only appears only on reel four.
The Treasure Chest’s ramped up cousin, the Golden Treasure Chest does the same but draws from a much richer pool of randomised gifts. The gifts in the Base Game are 7-21 free spins or 50-1000 coins for the Treasure Chest. On the other hand, the Golden treasure chest offers five random gifts from 250-10,000 coins, 7-21 free spins, Ragnarok free spins, and Rage Boost.
You can win seven free spins by charging up the rage meter for a given Viking. There are four Vikings, each of which will gain rage when you win with them.
During the free spins, the winning Viking is in Berzerk mode which allows them to always defeat the Siren. Defeating the siren makes every Viking in Berzerk mode become a fixed Wild for the rest of the free spins.
If you manage to gain full rage meter with more than one Viking at the same time you will receive 7 free spins for each Viking Berzerk mode, but they won't play out at the same time. The only exception to this rule is in case of the Ragnarok free spins. That's when all 4 Vikings turn into the Berzerk mode at the same time and you have the best chance for a spectacular win.
Alternatively, free spins can be won with the Free Spin symbol. Seven free spins for three symbols, fourteen for four symbols and twenty-one for five Free Spin symbols.
During free spins which are won with symbols rather than rage mode, you also win a randomly assigned "Bonus". There are five possible Bonuses: all the Vikings can be in berzerk mode, you can win one randomly placed stick wild, an entire reel of sticky wilds, 1 to 3 extra free spins or else you can win a mix of 5 Treasure Chests and Gold Treasure Chests.
There is also a Wild symbol that subs in for all symbols except the Free Spin or Treasure Chest symbols.

media.caption: Treasure Chest bonus from reel 4
Explanation of rage meter and bonuses in Vikings Go Berzerk slot

media.alt: Vikings Go Berzerk free spins bonuses
media.caption: Explanation of free spins bonus in Vikings Go Berzerk slot

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
Vikings Go Berserk is a very high volatility game in which the main game pays out small amounts and rarely. You really need to hit one of the bonuses (ideally Free Spins with all the Vikings Berzerk) to turn a profit.
The return to player is 96.10% which is very middle of the pack.

media.alt: Vikings Go Berzerk low symbols paytable
media.caption: Low symbols paytable

media.alt: Vikings Go Berzerk top symbols paytable
media.caption: High symbols paytable in Vikings Go Berzerk

Conclusion.text:
Vikings Go Berzerk is a really great slot at the design level. It is great to look at, fun to play and has some imaginative and varied bonus features.
Its high volatility plays well with some of our preferred strategies. Only the mid-range return to player is less than truly stellar.
We can strongly recommend this slot.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Sakura Fortune has a romantic East Asian theme.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
A calming classically East Asian tune plays, filled with flutes, and delicate zither notes help establish the exotic atmosphere. A breathy flute note adds tension to spins, ensuring the moment is exciting.
On the reels, players will find jade lions, carved dragons, and plenty of Chinese coins. A sword wielding hero and a beautiful heroine with jewel-adorned hair also make an appearance. It is easy to imagine the pair of them in a fantasy story.
The most striking symbol is a princess entirely clad in red, her hair caught by the breeze. With her hand on her sword, she peers down at the players with an unmistakably royal air.

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:

The Sakura Fortune Respin feature is triggered when players land 2 full stacks of Wilds. The number of respins awarded is decided by the number of Wilds on the reels when the feature is triggered.

overview:
