about_game: Four fun dragons are up for a spin in this game with its RTP of 95.94% and low volatility.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Dragon Spin is a nice little slot from Bally, who have opted to take the visual style of Chinese Dragon slots and modernise them a bit with a new colour scheme (blue and orange, rather than red and gold) and a range of designs for the dragons.
The result is a slot that feels both brand new and yet strangely familiar. Most importantly, it manages to avoid the stereotyping that dogs so many East Asian themed slots.

media.alt: Dragon Spin free spins big win
media.caption: Big win in the Dragon Spin's free spins bonus game

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are excellent. As well as being rendered in a modern 3D style, this slot has been given a lot of flare by some talented artists. The four dragon symbols each have oodles of personality, which makes each dragon feel like a fully realised character.
The animations aren’t as flashy, but do the job they are there to do. They help make wins easy to read and add movement to the visuals to keep them interesting.
The music is a little off for a slot like this, a percussion-based soundtrack that feels more dance-like than suggestive of dragons or China. But it works well enough to make it not worth muting.

Gameplay.text:
The base game is a five reel slot with three rows and thirty paylines.
Dragon Spin also has a feature called Mystery Stacked Reels. At the start of each spin, a randomly chosen symbol (excluding Scatter symbol) is assigned to be stacked on the reels, creating opportunities to land wins across multiple win lines.
There are a range of bonus games (see below for full details) to keep players on their toes.
Overall, the gameplay feels like it is constantly changing in small ways that maintain the player’s interest.

media.alt: Dragon Spin with Mystery Stacked Reels feature
media.caption: Mystery Stacked Reels is present in both base game and free spins
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol.
The Scatter only appears on reel 2, 3 and 4. Landing a Scatter on all three reels triggers the Free Spin Bonus game.

title: Michael Jackson
overview:
Michael Jackson
    
        Play Michael Jackson demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Join Michael Jackson for the slot performance of a lifetime in this music themed slot. Excellent gameplay is accompanied by a solid RTP (96.01%) and medium volatility. The King of Pop is back!

Theme and Storyline.text:
Michael Jackson: King of Pop is a music themed slot from Bally. Centred around the singer’s extraordinary body of work and featuring several licenced songs performed by him, this slot is a fitting tribute to one of the most recognisable titans of popular culture from the last century. And one of the strangest.
The reels feature his iconic hat and gloves, and the Little Lord Fauntleroy ruffle and shoe combo that he moonwalked into the public’s heart on.
It also sports five of his biggest hits on the soundtrack and does not downplay his uniquely man-made facial features. This one is for the fans.

media.caption: Base game win

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Being a licensed product based around a money-making icon like Jackson, this slot machine has had plenty of money poured into its looks. The background is a stage light-show of 80s glamour glitter and all the symbols have been well chosen to reflect the iconography of Jackson’s stage persona, not his more troubling private life.
The animations are similarly glittery and bring the game to life. But the real coup for this slot is that they were able to get the real music of the legend to play while you spin.
Even more cleverly, the music only runs while the player is keeping things spinning, giving fans a motivation to keep those coins coming if they want to hear the end of Billie Jean.

Gameplay.text:
The gameplay for this slot is pretty straightforward. It sports a base game with five reels and three rows.
There are twenty five fixed win lines and, to keep things interesting, there are a selection of randomised Wild-based features, as well as a set of different bonuses, which are randomised by a wheel spin when triggered.
All this adds up to a game that is interesting, fun, and well paced.

media.caption: Gameplay video featuring Stacked Wilds

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Bonus and Scatter symbols.
The Scatter symbol is misleadingly labelled 'Jackpot' in the game’s literature. However, it is a Scatter symbol and pays out for two or more symbols anywhere on the reels during a spin. The payout runs from two times the players bet per line for two Scatters up to 2,500 times the player’s bet per line for five Scatters.
During the base game, Moonwalk Wilds and Stacked Wilds can be triggered. When Moonwalk Wild is triggered, two to five Moonwalk Wilds appear anywhere on reels two to five. These Wilds move one to the left every subsequent spin until they drop off reel one. If they move onto a spot where a Bonus or Scatter symbol would land, the symbol counts for both a Wild and the Bonus or Scatter symbol.
Moonwalk Wilds double the payout of any win they are involved in, while Stacked Wilds simply turns two full reels into all Wilds.
If the player lands one Bonus symbol on each of reels two to four, then the Bonus is triggered. The player gets to spin "The Wheel" to determine what sort of bonus they will receive. They can win either free spins, cash prizes of a range of sizes, or one of several cash prizes and a spin on a second wheel which applies a multiplier between x2 and x10 to the cash prize.
If the player wins free spins, they either get ten free spins with modified reels without Bonus or Scatter symbols on, or five free spins in which a pair of Wild Reels move from right to left each spin, starting with just reel five, then reels five and four, reel four and three, etc…

media.caption: Hit 3 bonus symbols and spin the bonus wheel

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.01%, right in the neighbourhood of our yardstick for average, which is a very rough 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.40 up to a maximum of $/£/€80.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium. Middling volatility makes slots like this somewhat weak matches for our slot machine strategies which target higher volatility where possible.

media.caption: High symbols paytable for Michael Jackson slot machine

Conclusion.text:
With its high budget looks and it’s pop classic sounds, Michael Jackson King of Pop has the makings of a great slot.
For fans of Jackson’s music, there is pretty much no other slot. For those who weren’t fans, there is still plenty of glitz and sparkle to entertain and captivate. Though the latter group might want to mute the soundtrack.
The RTP is average and the volatility medium, which means players shouldn’t be particularly put off, but might still want to hunt out something with a lower vig or bigger swings.
On the whole though, the well paced gameplay, coupled with the visuals and a pop star whose fandom they might belong to, could make this a great slot for the right player.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Cool Jewels combines the beauty of water crystals and the crystalline stones that make up actual jewels.
In an icy landscape, the player’s job is to match the grid of jewels to spin gold from the arctic wasteland. There’s not much plot to go with this. No real story, though there’s a friendly polar bear in the logo that makes the player understand they are not wholly alone in the dark northern realms.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are pretty good, with mostly smooth animations and bright clear symbols. The background and symbols are well drawn and the heads up display elements are similarly pleasant to look at.
There is a slightly clumsy attempt at motion blur on some of the fancier symbols as they fall. But on the whole the visuals of the slot give off a polished, professional feel.
The background music is a well chosen synth track that has the kind of spangly, echoing tone of an ice cave. Coupled with this are the sound effects for the win and spin, which combine to generate a powerful sense of atmosphere.

Gameplay.text:
Cool Jewels is a grid based slot in which each spin randomises a six-by-six square of symbols. Groups of four or more of the same symbols connected vertically or horizontally form winning combinations. As with most games, the more symbols in a combo the bigger the win.
Each winning combination is then removed from the grid and then symbols above fall down to create new combos. This is called a cascade. A spin ends when there are no new winning combinations. Each cascade event increases the chance of the player triggering the bonus game.
Along with the bonus (see below for details), there are a range of fun game features to keep players interested, many of which are based around the varying kinds of Wilds (see below for more on that too).
Overall, gameplay is smooth and well paced. A definite plus for this slot.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There are four different kinds of Wild. The Unstable Wild, Shattering Wild, Shocking Wild, and Persisting Wild. The Wild symbols acts as substitute for all symbols except the other kinds of Wild.
Each of the four kinds of Wild have different properties. When multiple Wild types are part of the same winning combination, they trigger additional features that affect the grid until the end of that round.
Four or more Bonus symbols destroyed triggers the free spin bonus. Wilds can work to create a winning combination with Bonus symbols, but they do not count towards the number of Bonus symbols destroyed.
For example, if a group is formed of three Bonus symbols in a line, followed by a Wild, then another Bonus symbol, then they form a line of five and count as a winning combination. However, only the four Bonus symbols in that line of five symbols count towards the number of spins the player receives.
Four Bonus symbols in a group award 8 free spins. Five Bonus symbols award 10 free spins. Six award 15, and seven award 20.
Free spins can be retriggered.

media.caption: One of the enhanced features, that includes two identical Wild symbols

media.caption: Big win in the Free spins bonus. Cool Jewels also uses left column as a paytable indicator.

Conclusion.text:
Cool Jewels is a fun, well made slot with some lovely features.
The visuals are excellent, a kind of ice based Candy Crush layout with a more grown up style and far better graphics. The gameplay is slick, fast paced and varied. The bonuses are fun and the randomised features imaginative.
Even though it won’t work well for our preferred slot strategies, players who are unconcerned about maximising volatility may still find much about this game to be enjoyed.
Overall, this is an excellent slot.

Theme and Visual Details.text:
As you already guess from the slot name the theme is about pet fish. The reels of the game are set inside an aquarium with different kinds of fish swimming in the background. The symbols have a decent level of details but the slot lacks modern animations.
But even so the game has an attractive appearance thanks to the vibrant choice of colors. To make the slot even more fun to play the designers added a hip background music which perfectly flows with the game theme.

media.caption: Gameplay video with the Red Fish bonus feature

Bet size and payouts.text:
Goldfish is a 25 winlines slot with 5 reels and 3 rows, but the bet size in the game can range from $0.35 up to $105 per spin. The extra $0.10 to $30 is added to the total bet size as a feature bet. The higher the feature bet is the higher the payouts can be in the bonus features.

Low symbols paytable in Goldfish slot

Bonus features.text:
The Wild symbol in the game is the Goldfish. It can land on all reels substituting for all game symbols, except for the Scatter Fish Food symbol.
The Scatter symbol can also land on all of the reels and once 3 or more of them hit the screen the Fish Food Feature is triggered.
In this bonus round you are presented with a full screen of Fish Food Cans. You will need to choose among them and match 3 or 4 in order to get a prize. If you manage to find three Turtle Food Cans the prizes will be higher.
Players can also trigger five random features at the end of every spin. If the Goldfish feature is triggered you will get 5, 8, 10, 15 or 20 free spins with a win multiplier of x2, x3, x5, x7 or x10.
The Purple Fish feature is a cash bonus where the Purple Fish blows three bubbles on the screen. Each bubble contains a number from 0 to 9 and the numbers will align themselves on the reels to form one number from 15 to 984. This number is then multiplied with the line bet forming the total payout of the feature.
In the Red Fish feature you will need to choose among the Castle, Clam or Chest bubble. The fish will kiss the chosen symbol increasing its value with each kiss. The maximum prize per kiss is set at 200 times the line bet.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Invaders From The Planet Moolah is a royal mess in both the visual and technical spheres. However, it is hard not to be almost immediately charmed by its unique theme and story line.
The creators have built a pun from nothing – the planet Moolah be populated by intelligent cows who come to earth to abduct cow and man alike. This reverses the time-honoured tradition of aliens coming to earth and tipping cows or turning them inside out.
The earthlings, who are adorably represented here by an American rural family made up of Gramps, Gramma, a Cowgirl, and a MAGA looking hick, as well as cows of three different shades.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The characters are rendered in somewhat obvious styles, and the images are very badly optimised for smaller screen sizes. On larger screens, the slot still has the looks of an old fashioned sort of slot, but the world of the slot comes to life.
Above the reels, the cows in their spaceships bob cheerfully, each one with a different facial expression. Winning combos are beamed up by the cows and a nicely designed counter keeps track of the number of cascades.
The soundtrack goes with the visuals beautifully, borrowing ambient sounds and reel effects from the world of B-movie alien horror.

Gameplay.text:
The main game is a five by three slot with twenty five win lines. A cascade system is in place, which removes winning combos and allows new symbols to fall from above. This can result in additional wins.
The cascade system also acts as the trigger for the bonus game which is an interesting choice, though the Bonus is just a basic free spin game.
Players should also note that although there is a Jackpot symbol, it is just the highest paid symbol. There is no jackpot in Invaders from the Planet Moolah.

The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols. Wilds do not appear on reel one.
The Bonus game is triggered when a given spin results in four or more cascades. The number of free spins the player receives will depend on how many cascades happen on the triggering spin. Four cascades wins seven free spins, five gets the player ten free spins, six wins fifteen, and seven or eight cascades net the player twenty five and fifty free spins respectively.
The Bonus can also trigger at random at the end of a spin. When it does so, it will only award the player seven spins.

media.caption: Gameplay video

The features are limited but good enough to keep players interested, and the combination of an average RTP with very high volatility works well with our slot strategies.

title: Zeus God of Thunder
overview:
Zeus God of Thunder
    
        Play Zeus God of Thunder demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Zeus God of Thunder is a sharp-looking game with an RTP of 96.05% and medium/high volatility.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Zeus seems to get far more slots about him than any other Greek God. Being the King is nice work if you can get it.
In Zeus God of Thunder, the game plays to just one of Zeus’ most famous traits: the lightning bolts. It rather ignores the promiscuity and habit of disguising himself as animals.
The background is evocative of Greek architecture and hints at Olympian heights, while the reels are largely decorated with generic symbols including – for unfathomable reasons – a lion. The gods move in mysterious ways.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The visuals appear to have been designed with great technical prowess but are poorly directed.
For example, the Background that appears at random behind symbols is used to trigger the bonus game but disappears into the mess of symbols in a way that makes the reels hard to read and robs the player of the growing tension of each symbol falling.
The end result is that the slot is initially quite pretty to look at but doesn’t hang together in the way a slot should.
The audio aspects are excellent with a strong and varied soundtrack of both music and sound effect cues.

media.caption: Win in the Zeus God of Thunder slot

Gameplay.text:
Zeus God of Thunder is a five reel slot with four rows and thirty win lines.
The main spark of innovation is in the way the Bonus Wheels work (see below for full detail) and an Extra Bet feature can be activated, which increases the bet by 50% and increases the number of Backgrounds and Wild symbols in the base game and Free Spins available on the Bonus Wheels.
Beyond this, the gameplay is pretty typical and will not surprise any seasoned slot player.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all other symbols.
If three or more symbols with the Background appear in adjacent reels and the same row, this triggers the Bonus feature. The player then gets a spin on the relevant wheel ("three in a row", "four in a row", etc…) and is awarded a bonus based on the spin’s outcome.
There are three possible Bonuses that can be won in the wheel. For the two lower-end wheels there is an additional symbol that wins you a spin on the wheel one "in a row" up.
The first bonus that can be won is Free Spins. More spins are available the higher the "in a row", from four to five spins for 3 in a row or six to twelve for the five to six reels. These numbers are higher if the player has the Extra Bet active.
The other bonuses are one spin with extra Wilds and a selection of Jackpots that, like the free spins, are higher the more in a row the player hits and if the Extra Bet is active.

media.caption: Spin on the 'three in a row' wheel

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.05%, as close as makes no difference to our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.50 without the Extra Bet and $/£/€0.75 with the Extra Bet active. This goes up to a maximum of $/£/€75 per spin with the Extra Bet active.
The volatility of this game is medium to high. This makes it a reasonable match for our preferred slot machine strategies, which target higher volatility slots.

media.caption: High paying symbols of the Zeus God of Thunder slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Zeus God of Thunder is an interesting slot. The visuals and music are solid and the underlying maths is decent with an RTP of 96.05% and volatility in the medium to high range.
Another source of attraction for us is the system of Jackpots and Bonuses which is a fun combination and works to really elevate this game.
We strongly recommend this game.

title: China Mystery
overview:
China Mystery
    
        Play China Mystery demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: An average RTP (96.10%), low volatility, poor gameplay and lazy visual design make this China-themed game a hard-pass for us.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Konami’s China themed slots are largely interchangeable to the degree that China Mystery and China Shores, another of their slots, both use largely the same set of images for their low and medium value symbols.
The main difference this time around is a lack of pandas and a blue background instead of green.
There isn’t much storyline going on in these slots, but the central theme is generically Chinese imagery. Square-holed coins and women in conical farmer’s hats are the identifying images in China Mystery.

media.caption: Win in the China Mystery slot machine

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The real mystery is where Konami’s budget went on this. While their video game branch puts out triple-A games like the Metal Gear series, their slot machine branch produced a rather plain-looking slot.
The art is uninspiring and is rendered in almost exclusively ugly shades of each colour. There is almost no animation to speak of except for the reel spins and a flashing line to indicate a win.
There is no musical soundtrack, and only the most basic of sound effects, which add nothing to the atmosphere or tone of the slot machine. The Ode to Joy kicks in after the free spins, but this is too little, much too late. And German classical symphonies are hardly in keeping with an East Asian aesthetic.
As a result, the front end of this slot is unattractive and does very little to hold its audience’s attention.

Gameplay.text:
China Mystery is played on five reels with three rows and thirty fixed win lines.
There is no gamble feature and only one bonus which is made up of free spins (see below).
The gameplay, therefore, is very basic. Where some slots embrace this as an advantage, here it just adds to the feeling that not much effort was put into the player’s experience of this slot when they were designing it.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols and does not appear on reel one.
Three or more Bonus symbols trigger a Free Spin bonus with eight spins for three symbols, ten for four, and fifteen spins for five symbols. Additional bonus symbols result in even more spins, and can occur during Action Stacked Wilds. Additional free spins can also be won during the Free Spins themselves.
Any winnings the player manages to nab during free spins are doubled.
Before playing the free spins, the player has a choice to make between accepting the free spins they have just won or taking a randomised one-off Credit Win made up of a random prize starting from 40 times the player’s bet per line.
Players can take this option at any point while they have more than 20 free spins left. Though the randomised prizes are reduced proportionately to the number of Free Spins the player has left.

media.alt: China Mystery free spins on multiple winlines
media.caption: You can hit free spins on multiple winlines in a single spin

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.10%. Our yardstick for average is roughly 96%, so this is in that sort of zone.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.30 up to a maximum of $/£/€75.00 per spin. A good spread that is unlikely to be a problem for most bankroll sizes.
The volatility of this game is low, which makes it a very bad match for our slot machine strategies, as our slot strategies make use of high volatility.

media.caption: Top paying symbols paytable for China Mystery Slot

Conclusion.text:
Dull to look at, and duller to play, China Mystery has very little to recommend it, and the average RTP doesn’t do much to make up for the many shortcomings.
For players who are planning to use our preferred strategies, the low volatility makes this game of very little use.
We do not recommend this slot.

title: China Shores
overview:
China Shores
    
        Play China Shores demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: An unfortunate lack of imagination means China Shores has very little to offer the player except a middling RTP (96.10%) and medium volatility.

Theme and Storyline.text:
When Japanese game makers Konami design a slot called China Shores, you might have expected there to be an element of the local rivalry between the two nations in its design. Instead, China Shores only differs from the average China-themed slot in that the main colour scheme is green rather than red and gold.
The reels are decorated with symbols that contain panda’s faces, golden turtles and the Chinese character for "Good Luck" printed upside down – the symbol for "Arrives" looks a lot like the upside-down "Good Luck" symbol and so is a sort of visual pun indicating the arrival of good luck.
So not a particularly new take on the Chinese slot. This one will have to depend on its graphics and Jackpot system to stand out.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Unfortunately, the graphics are not going to be China Shores’s saving grace. The panda, though cute, is not very well drawn and the colour scheme feels garish.
The animations are basic. Just lines to indicate wins and a simple spin animation. This is also reflected in the sound design where the slot almost feels broken so spare are the sound effects.
Perhaps wisely given the rest of the design decisions, Konami opted not to give China Shores a musical soundtrack.

media.caption: Win in the China Shores slot machine

Gameplay.text:
China Shores is a five-reel and three-row slot with thirty winlines.
There is a two-tiered jackpot system which is triggered at random. Players at higher stakes are more likely to hit the jackpots.
The jackpot is the main appeal of the game which otherwise is pretty basic. It sports no gamble feature, just a single free spin bonus, and little else.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Bonus symbol.
Three or more Bonus symbols trigger a Free Spin bonus with eight spins for three symbols, ten for four, and fifteen spins for five symbols. During free spins, all of the player’s winnings have a times two multiplier applied to them.
However, before playing the free spins, the player is made an offer: either play the free spins or accept a randomised one-off Credit Win. The Credit Win can be between 32 and 234,000 times the bet per line, though the weighting is towards the lower end.
Players who chose the free spins have an opportunity to go back to the Credit Win if they have more than twenty free spins left. In that situation, they simply accept the Credit Win and will be exited from the free spins.

media.alt: China Shores Balance of Fortune options
media.caption: Players pick between Credit Prize and Free Game in the Balance of Fortune

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of the base game is just 88.90% if the jackpots are not included, which is incredibly low. However, with jackpots included, the RTP is 96.10%, very close to what we consider the average – 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.30 up to a maximum of $/£/€60.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a moderately good match for our preferred slot machine strategies since our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility in the slots we chose.
However, because players at higher stakes are more likely to hit the jackpots, the actual volatility increases as the player’s stake decreases.

media.caption: Top paying symbols for China Shores slot

Conclusion.text:
China Shores is an underwhelming slot. The visuals are not great, and are applied to a tired old theme. No one has made the effort to elevate the slot with interesting animations or immersive sound effects.
The main appeal is that you can win big with the jackpots, but even here the jackpot pool is much lower than the pool provided by slots that are more popular like EGT’s series of Hot slots.
The final nail in China Shore’s coffin is its low volatility and poor base game RTP. We do not recommend this slot.

overview:

about_game: For something with “action” in the title, this slot is a major snooze fest with a low RTP (95.16%) and medium volatility.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Action Bank is built around a strange pairing of bank robbery and tic-tac-toe. The reels have a small number of unrelated symbols (see below for fuller details) including a joker, noughts and crosses, and a lucky seven.
Against this, the entire bonus is based around busting into a massive bank vault. So one is left with a somewhat confused sense of what the designers were going for.

media.alt: Action Bank slot 5 of a kind win
media.caption: Win in the Action Bank slot machine

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are squarely in the "churn out skins for our software" category. The background is a simple brushed steel image, the reels are a standard grid with a few rivets around the edge for flavour.
On the reels, the selection of symbols are simple and set into plain backgrounds.
Animations are just for illustrating the spin and clarifying the win. The soundtrack follows the same cues and offers little of their own character to proceedings. The general impression is of a slot in which every part was designed by different people with a general brief to make things boring.

Gameplay.text:
The base game is a five-reel slot with three rows and twenty winlines.
The main innovation is to slow play down by including a non-winning "Nought" symbol. This acts simply to spread wins out. But despite this feature which could have emphasised high volatility, this remains a medium volatility slot.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol.
Each Nought symbol on a reel has a chance of transforming into a Scatter symbol, with a maximum of one Scatter per reel. If the player gets five Scatters, that is one on each reel, they are awarded a free spin bonus.
The player then has an opportunity to trigger the Big Bank Bonus or to gamble to win more a larger number of Free Spins. The total number of free spins awarded by gambling run from 5 to 30 in increments of 5.
During the Free Spin bonus, doubled symbols are added to the reel. The doubled symbols apply a multiplier of x2 to any wins that involve that symbol. Free spins can be retriggered.
If the player triggers the Big Bank Bonus, they are given a picking game in which they choose from fifteen bank vaults. Six of the doors have sapphires behind them, five have rubies, and  four have diamonds. The player is awarded the prize associated with the first gem they collect three of. The sizes of the prizes are in order of rareness.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 95.16%, well below our yardstick for average of roughly 96%. This counts strongly against this slot.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€400.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium. So it isn’t a great match for our preferred slot machine strategies. We prefer the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Paytable of the Action Bank slot machine

Conclusion.text:
The RTP alone precludes a recommendation. The vig is just too high.
However, it is not much of a loss. The slot is not especially interesting to play, nor to look at. The design is inconsistent and tedious, while the gameplay is basic.
Even without the low RTP, this slot is just terrible.

Theme and Visual Details.text:
The game has a Jewel theme with luxurious symbols across the reels. The visual details are not on the top level and there are hardly any animations available to give the slot a more appealing design.
Still the game symbols are enough to give the slot an aura of wealth and treasure waiting to be picked from the reels.

media.caption: In Crown Gems you can win even on middle 3 reels

Gameplay.text:
The gameplay in Crown Gems can be quite dull at times. The payouts come seldom so there’s not too much excitement on the reels.
But when a payout does land it’s usually medium or big and players can always use the Big Bet button for an instant dose of excitement.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Bet sizes and payouts.text:
The bet size in Crown Gems can range anywhere from $0.10 to $500 per spin.
This is a medium to high variance slot where the RTP value can go from 95.05% up to 96.08%, depending whether you use the Big Bet feature or not.
Like we mentioned earlier the slot doesn’t have a classic bonus feature.
This is a 10 payline slot but what makes the game interesting is the fact that you only need 3 or more adjacent symbols on a winning payline in order to get a payout. It doesn’t matter if they start from left to right, right to left or on any other reel as long as they are adjacent one to another.
Working in favor of this design is also the fact that all of the symbols can land stacked across the reels giving the player a chance to land a bigger number of winning combinations.
The only somewhat feature in the game is the Big Bet Spins. This feature allows you to buy 5 Big Bet Spins at the cost of $20, $30, $40 or $50.
In accordance with your purchase the Big Bet Spins are played on 20, 30, 40 or 50 active paylines. This is where the biggest payouts in Crown Gems can happen.
Risking $50 on 5 spins may sound too steep for some players but the feature can pay a lot more in return considering the fact that you are playing on 50 paylines with a bet of $1 per payline.

Big Bet Spins purchase gives you up to 40 extra paylines
5 of a kind win on full 50 paylines

Conclusion.text:
At first look Crown Gems seems like a simple slot with low-level visual details and non-existing bonus features. But as in most other Barcrest slots the designers have something extra installed under the bonnet.
We can freely say that this slot is reserved for those players who aren’t afraid to risk a bigger balance in order to win more in return. The Big Bet Spins offer exactly this. You will need to risk $50 on only 5 spins, but this is when the biggest payouts can happen.

title: Fu Er Dai
overview:
Fu Er Dai
    
        Play Fu Er Dai demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Join the silver spoon brigade in Fu Er Dai, a Chinese slot themed around young wealth. The high volatility and RTP of 96.00% appeal and so does the simple but solid gameplay.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Fu Er Dai – literally "two rich generations" – is a Chinese term for people who are born into money.
The slot machine runs with this theme, with symbols on the reel including an obnoxious but stylish jerk, diamond-encrusted cell phones, and expensive wallets. There’s even a symbol that is just a fat wallet full of credit cards sitting on a fan of cash.
It taps into the same kind of aspirational urge that made shows like Gossip Girl and The OC big hits and does so pretty well.

media.caption: Win in the base game

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics for Fu Er Dai are pretty good, with plenty of flashy animations to catch the eye and help make winning feel like an event.
The art style is solid, although the reels and background are rather classier than the symbols which feel a little tacky.
The music is pretty good, evoking a kind of modern twist on the typical "Chinese slot" style of music. It goes well with the world hinted at by the choice of symbols and theme, and ties together the whole slot into one coherent atmospheric piece.

Gameplay.text:
Fu Er Dai’s gameplay shows a kind of stripped-down elegance that is in stark contrast to the taste of its main characters. The base game is a typical five reel by three row affair with ten win lines.
The Scatter and Wild symbols’ roles are condensed into one, and the bonus feels like an extension of the respin system rather than a separate game (see below for details). This adjusts the pace of play and creates variety and continuity at the same time.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all other symbols.
When one Wild lands during a spin, it expands to fill the reel (transforming from a dragon into a girl as it does so), and triggers a respin.
If two or more Wilds land during a spin (or the player hits a second Wild during a respin) then a Free Spin Bonus of five free spins is triggered.
During the Free Spin Bonus, Wilds remain sticky for the following spin. They then continue to be sticky if another Wild is hit on the following spin. Each Wild that lands also adds an additional free spin to the remaining free spin counter.
There is a maximum of 20 free spins per Free Spin Bonus.

media.alt: Fu Er Dai free spins bonus with 2 Wilds
media.caption: Win Spin (free spins) bonus is triggered by 2 wild symbols

media.alt: Fu Er Dai single spin big win
media.caption: Big win in the free spins bonus

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.00%, right in the middle of the rough target area we treat as average.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is high, which makes it a perfect match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.alt: Fu Er Dai high symbols paytable
media.caption: High symbols paytable for Fu Er Dai slot machine

Conclusion.text:
With an average RTP and high volatility, this game works pretty well with our preferred strategies. And if you can get past the failed attempts at taste which the symbols show, the game has elegant mechanics and tasteful simplicity in its workings. Never judge a book by its cover.
This moderately popular slot by Play'n GO probably deserves a wider fanbase. We certainly recommend it.

title: Reactoonz
overview:
Reactoonz
    
        Play Reactoonz demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: A solid cascade based game from Play’n’Go, Reactoonz takes you to an alien world and feeds up fast-paced, varied action, and high volatility with an RTP of 96.51%.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Reactoonz takes you into a strange world of jelly-like monsters presided over by a serenely smiling alien creature. These adorable little critters combine onscreen to make winning combinations for you and in the process fuel the alien’s bonus powering energy orbs.
It is a little difficult to work out what kind of story serves as context for this world, but it is easy to say that it is a world that is a lot of fun to look at and mess around in.

media.caption: Symbols in Reactoonz slot take form of various monsters

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are beautifully rendered and come with plenty of flavour animations for wins, bonuses and the many dials and counters which fill up over the course of gameplay. The result is a visual feast in which there is always something to look at and plenty of surprises waiting around the corners.
The music like many slot machines is a bit invasive and repetitive but if you don’t like it, it is easily turned off and the rest of the sound design is a delight with all manner of sci-fi whooshes and pings.

Gameplay.text:
Powered by Play’n’Go software, Reactoonz is one a growing family of slot machines that are making use of the sophistication of computer software to change up the typical reel based slot machine. Here the mechanic is a cascade, where the monsters fall down as tiles onto a seven by seven grid.
Winning combinations – which are made up of any 5 or more matching monsters that touch horizontally or vertically – are removed from the game and the tiles above them fall allowing opportunities for new combinations to form. If the new tiles trigger another win it all goes into your win for that "spin".
On top of this are a series of fun bonus features which are described in full below.
Overall the gameplay works well with the visuals to make for a fun, constantly changing and very flashy slot machine.

media.caption: Same 4 symbols in 2x2 grid change into Giantoon symbol with a multiplier
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There are a number of bonus outcomes. Rather than being triggered by symbols they are triggered by specific game outcomes.
If you win nothing on a spin, the alien (known as Gargantoon) may drop four to eight wild symbols onto the grid.
There are also a series of what are known as "Quantum Features". These result from charges which are generated when you win. If you win enough times in one spin to trigger a Quantum feature, they will trigger. There are four Quantum features which have effects ranging from destroying all the one-eyed monsters on the grid, to turning three to six symbols wild at random and destroying the adjacent symbols (see the image for full details).
Every spin a random type one-eyed monster is selected and highlighted. If any of the highlighted monsters are part of a win, when they are removed from the grid, they leave behind two Wild symbols.
Wild symbols only appear when triggered by an event.
You can also win multipliers should four of the same symbol fall in a square shape. A two by two square results in a large x2 monster called a Giantoon that them occupies that space. The Giantoon counts as four symbols for the purpose of payouts.

media.caption: Bonus features are called Quantum features in Reactoonz slot machine

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The RTP of 96.51% is more or less the industry average and so doesn’t impress but also doesn’t detract.
The game is highly volatile, rarely paying out much on any given spin but with the occasional monster win.
The maximum win is 4570 times your bet per spin.
Bet sizing is done on a bet per spin system which makes calculating payouts easy but limits the amount of control you have. While this depends on the site you use, the one we tested allowed a range between £/$/€0.20 and £/$/€100.00 with a series of fixed bet sizes in-between.

media.caption: Paytable of Reactoonz slot

Conclusion.text:
Reactoonz is a fun and stylish slot with a lot going on for those who like their games with constant action.
Behind the lively animation, there are also a few nice features and as solid RTP.
It is not the best game in its class, but it does a decent job of it, and seems to be doing well with players given its popularity.

overview:
Moon Princess
    
        Play Moon Princess demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Moon Princess is a high volatility slot with a decent RTP (96%) and charming anime-inspired design which add up to a slot we can highly recommend.

Theme and Storyline.text:
The slot world is full of knock off and copyright skirting titles, but few of them are done with such elegance and care for their source material as Moon Princess. Play'n GO's Moon Princess borrows the style and tone of Sailor Moon, an anime series based on the manga of the same name.
While Moon Princess does not offer much in the way of content to explain its world, the characters come through vibrantly. Each of the "Princesses" has a magical power (which works as a fun feature on the reels) and a Japanese schoolgirl outfit.
For fans of the anime – or for those who enjoy a more Polly Pocket-like visual scheme – Moon Princess creates a familiar, but still fun and upbeat, world in which to lose yourself.

media.caption: Big win in the Moon Princess slot

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The design elements of this slot are all excellent. High-quality visual design is coupled with detailed and characterful animations.
The background of slowly drifting hearts complement the well-drawn and constantly mobile sprites, while the reels are full of bright and fun symbols. Animations provide constant motion, be it the winning cascades, the various counters, or the princesses themselves, everything is brought to life for the player.
Even the music is top notch. A pastiche of the Sailor Moon soundtrack with an ambient enough tone that it doesn’t become grating.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Gameplay.text:
Moon Princess pays out when a row of three or more symbols occur in a straight line, either vertically or horizontally.
Winning symbols are removed and the symbols allowed to fall down to form new winning combinations. Unlike in a typical cascade slot, in Moon Princess, no new symbols fall down from above the reels. Instead, after each cascade, the multiplier for all subsequent cascades in the current spin is increased by one.
If there are exactly three symbols in the winning combination, the middle symbol is not destroyed. Instead, it is transformed into a Wild.
There are plenty of additional features to keep things spicy. There are a number of counters and triggerable features, as well as a bonus in which the player can choose one of three games of varying volatility. These are described in full below.

media.alt: Moon Princes slot - Storm Girl Power activated
media.caption: Storm Girl Power picks and deletes 2 random sets of symbols from the grid

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols.
On non-winning rounds, one of three girl powers can be triggered: Love, who transforms one set of symbols into another; Star, who adds up to two Wild symbols to the reels; and Storm, who destroys two sets of symbols.
There is also a Trinity Counter which resets each spin. This Trinity Counter has three sections. For each set of three winning Princess symbols, one section fills up. For each set of four, two sections fill up. And a set of five will fill the counter in one go.
If the counter fills up, the reels are respun and then all three Princess Features are triggered in order on the new set of symbols. This feature is called the Princess Trinity and can be activated only once per spin.
When the player completely clears the grid of every symbol or if only Wilds are left on the reel, then the Free Spin Bonus is triggered.
The player is then offered a choice of three options, one for each of the Princesses. Depending on which option the player chooses, they will receive more or fewer free spins with differing features. The choices are designed so that the fewer spins the player receives, the higher the volatility will be.
During the Free Spins, any spin that does not include a win triggers the chosen Princess’s effect.
Filling up the Trinity Counter in the Free Spins will retrigger the Free Spins (up to a maximum of 20 free spins total).
Additionally, the multiplier does not reset between free spins, though it does max out at x20.

media.alt: Moon Princess slot Trinity feature activated
media.caption: Base game's Trinity feature is activated

media.alt: Moon Princess slot Free Spins feature
media.caption: Player can choose the volatility of Free Spins bonus game

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of 96% puts Moon Princess right in the middle of our range for roughly average.
The volatility, on the other hand, is far from average. This is an incredibly volatile slot, making it perfect for use with our slot machine strategies.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin.

media.caption: Paytable for the high paying symbols of the game

Conclusion.text:
Being a highly volatile slot with a decent return to player, Moon Princess is off to a good start. What really sells this slot, however, is the excellent design, high speed and varied gameplay, and the innovative bonus and feature systems.
We highly recommend this slot.

title: Viking Runecraft
overview:
Viking Runecraft
    
        Play Viking Runecraft demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: An excellent slot based around the mythology of the Vikings and designed to look beautiful and play well. A decent RTP of 96.7% and high-variance round out an overall highly positive slot experience.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Viking Runecraft draws on the mythology of the Old Norse tribes of Scandinavia and Iceland. With your play watched over by Thor, God of Thunder to begin with.
As the game progresses you will encounter not only his fellow gods, but many of the other mythical events (Ragnarok) and beasts (Fenrir the Wolf) from this body of myths.
Many of the figures from the game will be familiar in their Marvel universe forms, but some – like Jormungandr – might be new to most.

media.alt: Clear the rune pattern for a level up
media.caption: When you clear all symbols from particular pattern, Runes of Valhalla bonus is activated

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Viking Runecraft really stands out in its design features, not only are there numerous carefully designed backgrounds, all of which borrow their style from Blizzard’s hugely successful Warcraft series of games, but beautiful and varied animations.
The various features (on which you can read more below) are all given beautifully designed dials and readouts on the game’s heads up display.
The animations are smooth and varied, with intuitively structured readouts that are easy to get to grips with.
All in all it is one of the best looking and intelligently designed slots out there.

media.caption: Winnings are calculated from the same adjacent symbols instead of classic winlines system

Gameplay.text:
The gameplay of Viking Runecraft is a decided departure from the usual press button, spin reel, style play of your average slot.
Instead of reels it has a 7x7 grid of runestones and symbols which fall into place. You win when the symbols fall in groups of five or more. Symbols that are part of a winning combo are then removed and a cascade mechanic kicks in dropping new symbols into the newly empty spaces.
There is a level up system to entice you into playing a longer session, and as you move up through the levels the bonuses and randomised events (known as Gifts of the Gods) get better.

media.caption: gift of the Gods - game rules
Activated Odin's Gift of the Gods bonus
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The bonus system is almost wholly unique to Viking Runecraft. To encourage you to stick around this Play'n GO slot and play the various bonuses build over time.
For each level a pattern appears in the 7x7 grid. When your wins make use of one of the squares in the pattern it lights up. Light up the whole pattern over the course of your game and your level increases giving you a new god and new randomised events like additional wild symbols.
If you destroy more than 20 symbols on a spin, you trigger an event called Charge of Destruction. There are four Charges, each of which does something different:
Fury of Fenrir destroys two diagonal lines and turns two others into all the same symbols as those that triggered the event.
Judgement of Jormungander destroys a chain of symbols, apart from a few which are transformed into the same symbol.
Scorching of Surtr three random symbols are selected and the symbols around them destroyed. The selected symbols are then duplicated.
Lure of Loki destroys all of one symbol on the grid and transforms another into the trigger symbol.
If you destroy 40 symbols in a round, including those during the triggered event, then the Ragnarok bonus triggers in which all four events trigger one after another. Each one is triggered when no further wins are made with the previous one.
Multipliers are added to certain symbols during Ragnarok.
The third bonus after Charge of Destruction and Ragnarok are the Runes of Valhalla. The Rune Stone symbols trigger a counter when you with with five or more of them. If you have at least one rune when you level up you trigger the Runes of Valhalla. This is a wheel with the five rune stone symbols on it. Hit an activated stone to win.
The more symbols you go in with the better your odds.

media.caption: Bonus game rules explanation - Charge of Destruction
Scorching of Surtr, one of the Charge of Destruction bonuses is activated
Judgment of Jormungandr, another of the Charge of Destruction bonuses is activated
When you destroy enough runes by winning, another bonus opens for you
Another bonus of this interesting game - Runes of Valhalla

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The RTP of 96.70% is not bad, falling around the rough industry average for online slots.
Much more attractive than this is the high variance of the game, which allows for rare huge wins, rather than frequent small ones. We prefer high-variance games like this for our recommended slot strategies.
The bet sizes are rather limited though, you can bet 0.5 coins up to 2.50 coins so if your chosen site doesn’t provide a wide range of coin sizes you’ll find yourself very limited.

media.caption: Viking Runecraft's full paytable

Conclusion.text:
Viking Runecraft is a really excellent slot.
Decent RTP and high-variance make it mathematically attractive but the real draw is the excellent game design, fast and varied gameplay, and visually stunning backdrops and animations.
We can recommend this slot wholeheartedly.

overview:

about_game: The Fire Joker slot may have an average RTP of 96%, but its features are its redeeming qualities. The Respin of Fire ignites every player’s enthusiasm, but the rewarding potential of the Wheel of Multipliers triggers the top payouts.

Fire Joker review.text: The Fire Joker online slot has only been released a couple of years back by Play’n GO, yet it has since managed to appeal to a wide and varied player range, making it a desirable addition to any online casino game collection. If there is any doubt in this title’s earned status, a quick preview of its main segments and features is bound to disperse it.

Theme and Storyline.text: As the name suggests, the Fire Joker slot definitely deals with the theme of Joker, the popular card in card decks that has numerous application in all kinds of games, online slots included. Due to the nature of the slot which aims towards simplicity for the most part, the theme of the Fire Joker is not accompanied by a fully fledged back-storyline. Nevertheless, there are just enough elements of the slot’s main character, the Joker and its fiery nature that players are still up for an immersive yet simplistic experience.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The Fire Joker slot’s graphics visually illustrate what has just been said – a simplistic approach that allows players to experience the slot without any hindrance from additional features and details. Still, considering that the slot has only been released in 2016 rather than the early beginnings of these 3-reel machines, its design and effects, both sound and animation are modernized and highly functional.
The slot’s reels are thus set against a rhombic-like pattern in vibrant red and orange shades, indicative of the joker’s usual dress style. A catchy tune is also integrated in the reel spins, although players can freely set it to mute through the settings button. Ultimately the fire animation effect that is constantly illuminating the bottom of the slot screen adds just the right amount of novel design techniques to a classic structure, that is a 3-reel slot.

Gameplay.text:
The modern elements of the Fire Joker slot title are most evident in its gameplay, taking place on the 3x3 reel grid equipped with 5 fixed paylines. Every time the player hits a winning combination of 3 symbols on an active payline, the lower part of the screen reveals the fire and marks the win. Usually, you would expect the double up (gamble) feature to come between, but this slot does not offer this option as part of its gameplay.
The symbols are further supportive of the slot’s standard 3-reel nature, with a symbol selection comprised of several fruits – cherries, lemons, grapes and plums, the blue X, the BAR, star and Lucky 7 symbols, and ultimately the jackpot. The Joker, aside from the max symbol payout potential of 80 coins for landing 3 on a payline, further functions as a Wild symbol on the Fire Joker reels, substituting all others in order to make a the best winning combination.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Bonus features.text:
This slot provides its player base with two inter-related bonus features, the initial being the Respin of Fire. The feature has been added to increase payout potential, and to remedy the inconvenient, yet rather common occurrence of hitting stacked symbols on two reels without landing any winning combination. Thus, the Respin of Fire is triggered in such a case when any two reels are stacked with identical symbols, rewarding the player with one free respin for a chance to get the third stacked reel.
If all three reels across the slot’s grid are stacked with identical symbols, the Fire Joker’s Wheel of Multipliers bonus feature will be activated. This opens an additional screen with a wheel-of-fortune model that has 2x to 10x multiplier options on its fields – all players need to do is give it a spin and make use of its massive payout potential, the maximum reaching 800x the player’s stake.

Bet size and payouts.text: Fire Joker’s gameplay is available both in demo and real money mode in order to meet players’ gameplay preferences. In this regard, bet sizes vary from €/£/$0.05 to €/£/$100, with a maximum win of 800x in best case scenario.

media.caption: Top symbols paytable for Fire Joker slot machine

RTP and Variance.text: An RTP of 96% has been calculated for this slot. With a medium variance, it provides a rather optimal gameplay for the usual classic slot fan.

media.caption: Lowest symbols paytable

Conclusion.text: Play’n GO are sure to consider the Fire Joker slot as one of their more popular and accepted releases, even more so due to its availability across platforms. The few yet rewarding effects and features and immersive gameplay of this 3-reel slot perfectly fits the smaller screens of mobile and tablet devices, although PC fans are just as quick to accept it.

overview:

about_game: Don your armour and charge up your mana in this fantasy-themed slot, which uses unique game mechanics to deliver a magical experience.

Theme and Storyline.text:
At first glance, Tower Quest looks to be a straightforward high-fantasy themed slot. It has armoured elves, vicious-looking orcs, dragons, wizards, and potions galore.
Beneath all of this are hints of Magic: The Gathering, These hints blossom to fullness in one of the bonus games, which sports card and dice-based gameplay.
If you’ve ever wanted to storm the dark tower and defeat the evil wizard now you can do that in slot form.

media.alt: Tower Quest card battle bonus game
media.caption: Pick your fighter for a card battle against the wizard

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are one of Tower Quest’s big selling points, with a strong collection of characters as symbols on the reels and interesting world-building featured in the artwork and backgrounds.
There are plenty of animations, with every win and spin coming with unique animations for each symbol. Little wisps of magic float from the reels to the counters when the Potion symbols land (more on that later).
The soundtrack is a sparkling mix of cinematic digital orchestras with some metal riffs underneath for the moments when things kick into high gear, like during the bonus rounds.

media.alt: Tower Quest blue scatter bonus game win
media.caption: Big win from the blue scatter symbol bonus game

Gameplay.text:
Tower Quest is a five reel slot with three reels and twenty fixed win lines.
The main appeal of the game is in the various bonus features which use unique mechanics and give the player a great deal of choice in how and when they are triggered (fuller details below).

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Blue Scatter, Red Scatter and Bonus symbols. The Wilds are three symbols high and so there is a chance of landing multiple Wilds when the player does hit one.
There are three Bonuses. One which is triggered by hitting three Bonus symbols and two which depend on the Scatter and are triggered by the player themselves.
The Scatter based bonuses use the counters either side of the reels. Each Red or Blue Scatter that falls is added to the counter. The player can trigger the bonus after certain thresholds. The later the threshold (and therefore more symbols they have accrued), the better the bonus.
This allows the player to take frequent small bonuses or wait longer between bonuses but get bigger ones.
For example, the player can trigger the Blue Scatter bonus after five symbols have accrued on the counter. In this case they receive one free spin with a middle reel locked in as all Wild. If the player waited until they had ten or fifteen symbols accrued they would still receive one spin, but for ten symbols the spin would have five of the regular symbols counting as Wilds, and for fifteen reels one, three and five are all Wild.
The Red Scatters have five spins with a times three multiplier for ten accrued symbols, and additional Wilds added for twenty and thirty accrued symbols.
The other bonus is triggered by hitting three Bonus symbols and results in a Magic the Gathering style combat game against the wizard with your winnings based on how well you do against the wizard’s deck.
As bonuses go these are some of the most interesting and surprising out there and really make this game stand out from the pack.

media.alt: Tower Quest blue scatter symbol bonus round
media.caption: Top tier bonus game from 15 blue scatter symbols

media.alt: Tower Quest red scatter bonus game win
media.caption: Win from the red scatter bonus game

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.00% which is more or less exactly our yardstick for average.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin. That should keep most questers happy, from the lowest squire to the fanciest of knights.
The volatility of this game is medium, meaning wins are moderately frequent, and aren’t likely to be especially large when they do come in. As a result, this slot is a weak match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.
The many other strengths of this slot may beat out strategic considerations though.

media.caption: Paytable for Tower Quest slot machine

Conclusion.text:
With clever gameplay and beautiful visual design, Tower Quest is a delight to play.
The RTP is 96%, which is pretty middle of the road and doesn’t do much to mitigate the medium volatility. This does mean that those who follow our preferred strategies might wish to look elsewhere.
For anyone else though, this is an excellent fantasy-themed slot.

title: GEMiX
overview:
GEMiX
    
        Play GEMiX demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Low volatility is the main drawback to this otherwise exciting and charming slot. The RTP is 96.75%.

Theme and Storyline.text:
GEMiX is a fun, fast paced slot set in a realm full of wizards, mining dwarves, and lollipop princesses. By completing patterns on the reels, you can move between various "worlds" of this realm in your hunt for jewels and gems.
The high-fantasy concepts are rendered here in a cartoonish and childish way, which feels a little out of place for a slot machine. This oddness of tone is rescued from the scrap heap by excellent visual design and some fun gameplay items that help draw the player into the world Play'n GO is creating.

media.caption: Clearing of the 3rd pattern of a world grants the World Bonus win

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
With its bright colours and cartoon characters, GEMiX could have chosen a very simple visual style. Instead, the grid is bedecked in well-rendered 3D gems, the numerous counters are all carefully drawn and animated to perfection, and each of the features, when triggered, involves a charmingly designed character appearing beside the reels.
The overall visual work on this slot is excellent. There is a lot going on, but it remains intuitive and pleasant to look at. And all this is customised for each of the three gameplay "worlds".
The soundtrack has the feel of a Saturday morning Hanna Barbera series and as such is both perfectly suited to the game and likely to be faintly irritating to most players.

media.caption: Supercharged win with x3 multiplier

Gameplay.text:
Instead of winlines and reels, GEMiX is played on a seven by seven grid. The player wins when a cluster of five or more of the same symbol forms. A cluster is a group of symbols connected either horizontally or vertically.
A cascade system results in winning symbols being removed and new symbols dropping in from above.
There are effectively three versions of the base game, one for each "world". The game moves between these worlds when the player fills out a pattern in the background of the reels. These patterns are filled out when the player has a winning symbol at least once on each of the squares in the pattern.

media.caption: GEMiX slot combines the cascade system and clustered wins
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbols substitute for all symbols and are triggered randomly. When a Wild is triggered, what happens next depends on what "world" the player is in.
In Miner’s world, up to ten Wilds are added at random to the grid. In the Princess’s world the Wild starts at an edge, then spreads one symbol at a time at random until it reaches another edge symbol. In the Wizard’s world up to eight Sticky Wilds are added. These Sticky Wilds do not drop down during cascades and are not removed if part of a winning combo.
Instead of a bonus game, there are a set of additional features which are triggered when a player destroys 20 symbols in one spin to fill up the Bonus meter. If the player destroys 40 symbols in one spin before triggering the meter, then an additional 3 times multiplier is added to their winnings for any subsequent wins during that spin.
The bonuses are:

media.caption: Princess' World random Wilds run from edge to edge
One of the Crystal Charge bonuses - Chain Lightning

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
GEMiX’s return to player is a roughly average 96.75%, putting it a little bit ahead of the average slot, which we estimate to have a return to player of around 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.50 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is low, making it useless to any player who intends to use our preferred slot strategies.

media.caption: Full paytable for GEMiX slot

Conclusion.text:
Unfortunately, despite a thoroughly enjoyable main gaming loop and an engaging visual style, GEMiX is let down by its low volatility.
While that means players who are pursuing our preferred strategies will want to give it a miss, players who do not object to a low volatility slot will find much to be enjoyed in GEMiX.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Rainbow Riches Pick’n’Mix takes the original Rainbow Riches slot – with its leprechaun imagery and idealised vision of an Ireland inhabited entirely by piskies and fae – and adds in a slew of extra bonus games to keep things interesting.
The theme is pretty sparsely fleshed out with the symbols on the main reels being almost entirely ace to ten symbols and a set of leprechauns. The background is a version of the Irish countryside rendered in candy kingdom colours with perfect red and white toadstools alongside a golden road.

Gameplay.text:

Theme and Storyline.text:
Ghost Slider is a bit of an oddball slot. It is a horror themed slot machine, which is not all that uncommon, but it is based around haunted paintings. This does stand out a bit. Haunted paintings are not an especially recognisable horror trope. Nor are the old fashioned ghosts in this slot all that frightening.
Yet everything else about the slot seems to be asking to be taken seriously. The array of tombstones at the top, the gloomy gothic background, the symbols on the reels.
Then the ghosts appear and the slot becomes almost comical. The theme is a bit of a misfire then. But it is certainly strange enough to catch our attention.

media.caption: Win in Ghost Slider's cascade system

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics fall into that rather ugly realm of trying to be realistic, but not quite having enough skill in the artists’ pool to pull it off.
This feels especially strange when you note that the animations are, in places, quite elaborate and varied. Though they are not much better than the basic artwork they are paired with.
The soundtrack is bizarrely out of kilter with the rest of the slot’s tone. Upbeat techno music kicks in when you win with what are meant to be frightening ghost symbols.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Gameplay.text:
Ghost Slider has five reels, each of which sports three rows. There are ten win lines for the player to hit.
The gamble system allows several options. Though the basic game is a double-or-nothing shot, players also have the option to cash out half at any point and continue gambling.
There is a cascade system whereby winning symbols are removed and new symbols drop down to take their place. This ties into the bonus system (details below), which is a simple but solid one.

media.caption: Ghost Slider offers also a second gamble feature, different from the usual red-black choice

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all other symbols.
If the cascade runs four times in a single spin, the free spin bonus is triggered. The more cascades, the more free spins, with a maximum number of 50 free spins.
This is a fairly simple setup, but it works quite elegantly and should satisfy players who aren’t looking for an "all frills" slot.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 95.91%, a little under our yardstick for average of roughly 96%, but not enough for us to significantly shift our view on this slot.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€20.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is at the high end of medium, which makes it a weaker match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Full paytable for Ghost Slider slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Ghost Slider is an unusual looking slot that could do rather better in the graphics department.
Under the hood it sports an average RTP, moderately high volatility, and a simple double or nothing gamble feature.
It’s a solid slot which is neither terribly impressive nor impressively terrible.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Loading up the slot is dark and neutral in tone, and the graphics aren’t over the top.
This is what we have come to expect from Merkur Gaming. The symbols are placed against a wooden set of reels, with hieroglyphics in the background.
Along with a plain gaming screen, the music has a light jingle that immediately stops between spins.
Although there aren’t many sound effects, the visuals and music may suit players who prefer substance over style.

Gameplay.text:
Set on a 5x3 gaming grid, Lucky Pharaoh comes with 10 fixed paylines and there is nothing too complicated about it.

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:

title: The Big Easy
overview:
The Big Easy
    
        Play The Big Easy demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: The Big Easy rapidly became one of the most popular titles at online casino slot selections since it was first made available to the public back in 2017, both due to the entertaining and highly rewarding aspects of the game as a whole.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Judging by the name of the game, indicative of the New Orleans-based movie dealing with corrupt officers, gangs and love, players are bound to expect many symbols of this city’s southern way of life.
Placing an emphasis on the theme of New Orleans’ key features – music, food and drinks – it aims to immerse players into the setting for full enjoyment.
The relaxed, easy-going attitude towards life that is characteristic of New Orleans is perfectly depicted in The Big Easy slot, as there is no plot twist storyline that would require players to concentrate too intently.
Here, all they have to do is set the tone and lay back with the glass of bourbon on the rocks spinning on the reels for one sweet payout after another.

media.caption: Single payline win - winnings are nicely visible

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphic design of The Big Easy slot game is a great example of Spielo’s ability to render the game with the best visual appeal. Namely, the 2-D reel elements, the reel backdrop set against the typical New Orleans landscape of typically southern streets and buildings, as well as the accompanying features – sound and animation effects, all contribute to the player’s general impression.
The former is a balance between smooth background jazz and sax spins, with numerous symbols to back the importance of music in this lifestyle, if it isn’t already evident from the range of music-inspired symbols on the reels.

Gameplay.text:
The Big Easy is a 5-reel slot game with 20 paylines that can be activated according to player’s choice in groups of 1, 5, 10, 15 and 20.
A single bet ultimately amounting to €100 is the most a player can bet per spin. In this regard, taking into account the many various symbols on the reels, with a different payout potential and other player-benefiting features, the gameplay is bound to appeal to a wider player profile range.
Namely, music is a constant inspiration in this slot, with many medium and high value symbols representing anything from instruments, through posters to actual stage performers – the poster, the sax, the piano keys, the trumpet performer and the lady singer are all representative of this theme.
As for food and drink, a plateful of seafood pays rather well, with 100x your single line stake should you land 5 on a paylineand the bourbon on the rocks symbol which pays only half of that.
The symbols representing the streets of New Orleans inevitably include the famous Bourbon St. which pays 150x your single line stake, while the performers are left to the higher classes. Namely, the slot allows players a glimpse into their stage appearances featuring a trumpet player and a lady singer symbol.
While these regular symbols do contribute to the gameplay, most of the payouts are inevitably attributed to the wins landed by the Wild and the Scatter.

media.caption: Gameplay video with Free spins feature

Bonus features.text:
Despite the relatively rewarding nature of the regular symbols on The Big Easy’s reel grid, there are two which trigger special features for even higher payouts. Namely, The Big Easy logo symbol is the Wild on the reels, with its main function being to replace all other symbols except the Scatter when landing in a winning combination.
As for the Scatter – the Moon symbol, it’s crucial to mention its rewarding potential, as 3 scatters result in a 4x bet multiplier, 4 scatters – 11x and 5 scatters – 20x the totalbet.
What is interesting about The Big Easy logo symbol is that it doubles as the bonus symbol, with a minimum of three logos on the reels triggering the Free Spins Bonus feature.
It is rather interesting, as players get to pick between Jazz clubs and thus determine the number of free spins they are awarded, while the following, instrument pick will determine the multiplier they get for the free spins wins.
A different range of clubs and instruments, i.e. number of spins and multipliers is available for combinations of 3, 4 and 5 The Big Easy logos:
3 logo symbols – Free Spins: 8, 10 or 15 & Multiplier: 2x – 4x;
4 logo symbols – Free Spins: 16, 18 or 20 & Multiplier: 5x, 6x or 10x;
5 logo symbols – Free Spins: 22, 24 or 25 & Multiplier: 7x, 8x or 10x.

media.caption: Special symbols of the game
How free spins multipliers work

Bet size and payouts.text:
As mentioned earlier, the slot’s reels feature lower and higher paying symbols, with the bourbon and the poster symbol offering the lowest payout of 50x a single line bet amount for 5 landing on an active payline, followed by the previously mentioned seafood and Bourbon St. symbols.
A payout of 175x bet per line is available for landing 5 of the street symbol; the same case scenario would see the sax symbol pay 200x bet per line, the piano keys – 250x, the trumpet player – 500x, and both the lady singer and The Big Easy logo symbols paying 1000x should all five land on an active payline.
Players can bet from 0.01 to 5.00 per single line, i.e. bet sizes per spin range from €0.01 (single active payline) to €100 (max 20 active paylines).

media.caption: Top symbols paytable

RTP and Variance.text: The slot’s RTP is calculated at 95.01%, a bit lower than the industry average. In terms of variance, the slot is categorized as medium to high variance, allowing players to make smaller bets and still hit bigger wins.

Conclusion.text: All in all, the city’s air, culture and way of life have definitely proven to be a suitable choice of theme when it comes to The Big Easy online slot title. Further emphasized by the individual symbols providing attractive payouts, this Spielo release definitely deserves its popularity ranks at online casino game selections.
