title: Pink Elephants
overview:
Pink Elephants
    
        Play Pink Elephants demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Pink Elephants and cute little hyraxes abound in this strange offering from Thunderkick. A middling RTP and volatility are the only drawbacks to this otherwise excellent slot.

Theme and Storyline.text:
While the phrase "pink elephants" is usually used as a euphemistic idiom for the hallucinations of drunkards, the game Pink Elephants is very much a real thing. Within a world populated by anthropomorphised rock hyraxes which are, as every lover of genetic trivia knows, the closest living relatives of the elephant family.
The heat-shimmering desert world in which these hyraxes live is the backdrop to this strange, fun, and oddly beautiful slot machine created by Thunderkick, which can be found in one of many Thunderkick casinos available online.

media.caption: You can hit up to 5 Mystery Scatter symbols

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The aforementioned background is a fine example of scene setting, the heat warps the abandoned elephant statues, and in the foreground the reels are done with real care. The characters are cute, the designs well wrought, and all in all the slot works well at the visual level.
The music is a strange and eerie piece of music with the rich warbling of didgeridoos underlying something reminiscent of Arabian brass and strings over the top. This generates an atmosphere that is hallucinatory, and plays into both the desert setting and the heffalump based theme.

Gameplay.text:
Pink Elephants is a six reel slot machine with four symbols to a reel. It operates on an any way pays system which means that any combination of matching symbols appearing anywhere on consecutive reels are a winning combination, so long as they start on the leftmost reel.
As a result there are 4,096 ways to win.
It comes with a few fairly standard features, and nothing in the gameplay is going to surprise an experienced reel-surfer. That said, what it does offer is well executed and covers all the key bases.

media.caption: Otherworldly animation starts the bonus game

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There is a Wild symbol which, as per usual, substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter and Mystery Scatter symbols.
In the base game the Scatter symbol will trigger the Bonus Feature if you hit three or more. The Bonus feature is made up of free spins. 7 free spins are awarded for three Scatters, up to 19 spins for hitting six Scatters.
In the Bonus feature two Scatters will add three spins with an extra 2 spins per extra Scatter up to a maximum of plus 11 spins for hitting six Scatters.
Mystery Scatters are triggered at random and result in 1-5 extra Scatters being added to the reels. They count towards triggering the Bonus.
During the Bonus rounds orbs can be collected for each high symbol. These fill up a meter for each of them, turning that symbol into pink elephants for the remaining free spins. Filling up a meter also rewards an extra free spin.

media.alt: Pink Elephants slot free spins win
media.caption: Big win from the single spin of the bonus game
How does Mystery Scatter symbol work

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
Pink Elephants’ return to player is a pretty average 96.10%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum of $/£/€0.10 to a maximum bet per spin of $/£/€100.00. A ten cent minimum should allow almost any low-stakes players comfortably manage their bankroll, while the maximum should satisfy those whose bankrolls are as vast and immane as the wise elephant herself.
The volatility of this game is medium. We would really like a higher volatility to match better with our preferred strategies, but while medium might not be great, it certainly isn’t bad.

media.caption: Explanation of the bonus game rules
Paytable for Pink Elephants slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Pink Elephants is a great slot at the level of visual design – creative, pretty and full of detail.
Behind the scenes the statistics are a bit more average middling volatility and RTP don’t excite us, but they also don’t turn us against the game completely.
Overall the game gets a recommendation from us, even though there are a few things that could be improved.

title: Dolphin's Pearl
overview:
Dolphin's Pearl
    
        Play Dolphin's Pearl demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Bland looking, dull to play and with a rather stingy RTP of 95.13%, Dolphins Pearl is certainly not the worst slot we’ve played, but it is really not very good. I guess it is not always better, down where it’s wetter.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Dolphin’s Pearl tells the tale of an intrepid dolphin and its ragtag team of sea life friends and their search for treasure under the sea. You get to play along with the dolphin, hunting for the pearls of the title and collecting the odd coin here and there along the way.
The characters (along with the underwater ace to nine symbols) are all rendered rather blandly and the pale blue background doesn’t make for the most attractive version of the ocean-going theme.
Still, the dolphin itself is pretty cute.

media.caption: Single winline win in Dolphin's Pearls slot

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are more or less what you would expect from a Novomatic slot of Dolphin’s Pearl age and the symbols are somewhat cheap looking digital art.
It also reuses the sounds, buttons and reel animations from a string of other Novomatic slots which were, like this one, simply reskinned versions of Book of Ra.
While not actively offensive, the graphics and sound are far from enticing.

Gameplay.text:
Gameplay is on a five reel basis with nine win lines of which you can play any number.
There is a black and red gamble feature allowing you to play double or nothing for your wins and some basic bonus and free spin features.
When betting all lines it is possible to win up to 500 times your bet per spin playing the gamble feature.

media.caption: The usual gamble feature from Novomatic is here as well
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There are two special symbols in Dolphin’s Pearl.
The first is the Scatter symbol which pays out between two times your bet per spin for hitting two symbols up to 500 times if you hit five Scatter symbols.
When you win with three or more Scatters, you also receive fifteen free spins with a 3 times multiplier for your winnings during those free spins.
The second symbol is the Wild dolphin symbol which can play as any symbol except the Scatter and adds a two times multiplier to any winning lines that are included.

media.caption: Nothing special about paytable of Dolphin's Pearls slot machine

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of 95.13% is rather low (although a common benchmark for Novomatic slots on this particular design).
The game does come with high volatility. To make a big win you really need to land the somewhat rare free spins bonus.
The website we tried playing on allowed a minimum bet of $/£/€0.04 to a maximum bet of $/£/€90.00 per spin.

Conclusion.text:
Dolphins Pearls is very unimpressive. Although no one feature is terrible, the entire game is bland and below average. The RTP is lower than the average of around 96%, the graphics cheap looking, the music is copied over from other Novomatic slots.
Only the very high volatility stands out, the rest is very disappointing.

title: Dolphin's Pearl Deluxe
overview:
Dolphin's Pearl Deluxe
    
        Play Dolphin's Pearl Deluxe demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Go for a swim with the dolphins in Dolphin’s Pearl Deluxe. A highly popular revamp of a classic game. Although it doesn’t do enough to solve the old game’s problems and is saddled with a poor RTP of 95.13%, it has a tasty free spin feature if you can hit it.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Dolphin’s Pearl Deluxe is a more or less unchanged update of Dolphin’s Pearl. Like the original, you play along with a treasure hunting dolphin and a collection of underwater creatures ranging from stingrays to angelfish.
There’s not a lot more to it, except that the goal is to get the pearl, which comes with the biggest rewards.

media.caption: Simple win in Dolphin's Pearl Deluxe slot

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The creatures have been given an art style upgrade which helps with one of the biggest downsides of the original which was that it was a bit unpleasant to look at.
The game is still pretty much the same software underneath including the sound design and animations as the original as a result it still suffers from feeling dated and clunky. The reel-sounds and win-sounds, in particular, were just about acceptable in the original but in the update without the mitigation of historical context just feel tacky and annoying.
Overall this is a more polished game than the original.

Gameplay.text:
The gameplay is a five reel, ten winline slots, a small change upwards from the original’s nine winlines. You can play any number of lines up to ten.
The only real variation on push button play is the gamble feature which is the Novomatic standard of a red or black game, in which you must choose the colour of the next card drawn off a deck. Thanks to the random number generator this is always a coin flip and is mostly used to increase volatility if that is your prefered strategy.

media.caption: Standard gamble feature from Novomatic
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There are two Symbols with additional features in Dolphin’s Pearl Deluxe.
There is a Wild symbol, the Dolphin of the title. This symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol and comes with a x2 multiplier for any wins it is a part of.
The Scatter symbol, the Pearl of the title. This symbol pays out two times your bet per spin if you hit two of them. Three or more gets you fifteen free spins as well as your payout. The payouts go up to five hundred times your bet per spin for five Scatter symbols.
During the free spins, a x3 multiplier is in effect. This is where the real money is to be made and is a major reason for the game’s high volatility.

media.caption: Award from 4 Scatter symbols hit is 15 Free spin rounds

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player is 95.13% for this slot machine. Lower than our benchmark for the average of around 96%. This is low enough to discourage us from playing it.
On the other hand, if you play a high volatility strategy this game is famous for large swings. You will want to account for the long dry periods however in your bankroll management.
The website we tried playing on allowed a minimum bet of $/£/€0.04 per spin up to a maximum bet per spin of $/£/€100.00.

media.caption: Dolphin's Pearl Deluxe paytable

Conclusion.text:
Dolphin’s Pearl Deluxe does little to draw a player in. The features are stale, overused and unimaginative. Even with the upgraded graphics, the game is not especially fun to look at and the low RTP is a dealbreaker.
Although we do not recommend Dolphin’s Pearl Deluxe, it should be noted that hitting it big on the free spins with the multipliers can make for an attractive prospect and the game remains popular with a large group of players.

title: Lucky Ladys Charm
overview:
Lucky Ladys Charm
    
        Play Lucky Ladys Charm demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: No RTP data is a worry with this slot, but not enough to put off the many punters who have made this slot immensely popular.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Lucky Lady’s Charms takes a selection of old superstitions about lucky objects and collects them together in a kitsch and tacky way. The horseshoes, four-leaf clovers, seven-spotted ladybirds, and ten-cent pieces are staples of slot machine iconography.
However, they are rarely so cheaply flung together. Lucky Lady’s Charm lacks character or style in the way the theme is put to use and as a result, fails to be as engaging as other slots that attempt the same sort of thing.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are the big letdown of Lucky Lady’s Charm. They look cheap, lack character, and exist in a bland void painted the ugliest possible shade of pink.
As well as ugly artwork, the other aspects of Lucky Lady’s Charm entirely fail to boost the slot's sense of atmosphere or style. There is no background music and the reel sounds are generic and tired.
Over all of this is laid a small set of dull, badly timed animations that mark out wins and provide a touch of movement during the spins.
Lucky Lady’s Charm, in other words, is utterly charmless.

Gameplay.text:
The base game is a simple five reel slot with three rows and ten win lines.
There is a simple gamble feature in which players can play a game of double or nothing. This feature does not affect the player’s expected return but does increase the volatility of the game.
There is also a very basic free spin bonus.
In other words there is nothing to make this slot stand out from the crowd in its game mechanics.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
Lucky Lady’s Charm has no Wild symbol. It does have a Scatter though.
The Scatter pays out for two or more symbols anywhere on any reel so long as they appear in the same spin.
If they hit three or more Scatters, the player will also trigger a bonus of fifteen free spins. During the Free Spin Bonus, a multiplier of times three is applied to all winnings.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
Developer does not list the return to player in the game’s documentation. Unlisted RTP data is a problem as it can allow companies to hide an extortionate vig.
At least one other review site lists the return to player as 95.13%, which is below average. However, they do not list their source so you will have to take that number with a pinch of salt.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.01, if you play one line, and goes up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin if you play all ten.
The volatility of this game is high, which would make it a great match for our slot machine strategies, which favour the highest possible volatility, if only Lucky Lady’s Charms were prettier or had a better return to player.

Conclusion.text:
Lucky Lady’s Charm is unlikely to seduce any player into trying their own luck playing the game. The first impressions are of an ugly, generic slot, with the most basic forms of gameplay.
Looking deeper the player is given no information on the return to player and only the high volatility proves of interest.
And yet there is an X-factor that seems to connect with people, as this slot is very popular.
We would suggest giving it a try and seeing if this lady to charms you.

title: Amazon's Battle
overview:
Amazon's Battle
    
        Play Amazon's Battle demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Go to war with the tribe of warrior women in Amazon’s Battle. Pleasant to look at, but not nearly as volatile as we would like.

Theme and Storyline.text:
The Amazons were a race of warrior women from early Greek myths. They first appear in some versions of the Iliad, arriving after Hector’s death to fight on Troy’s side. Amazon’s Battle turns them into tattooed axe-wielding hotties. With a pet tiger and on-point feathering in their haircuts.
The version has some of the pre-historic fantasy setting that Greek myth evokes but filtered through the aesthetic of 90s television. Amazons’ Battle is Troy for the Generation Xena.

media.caption: Win in the base game of Amazon's Battle slot machine

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Amazon’s Battle’s graphics don’t break much in the way of new ground. But they are decent looking. The artwork is well wrought and the symbols clear and fun. The variety of Amazons and their pet tiger make for a pleasant visual landscape, and the jungle backdrop is pleasant.
The animations are very simple, as are the win and spin sounds. There’s no background music to speak of, except for a quick sting when the player hits a winning combo.
But the sound effects match the animations and are good enough, if rather short on that vital sense of atmosphere that draws one into a slot machine.

Gameplay.text:
With thirty win lines on the five reel, three row slot, there are plenty of ways to win. Especially with the stacked symbols on each reel.
Players looking to ramp up the volatility can do so with a gamble feature. A simple red or black choice, with a double or nothing bet.
The gameplay might be a little basic but there’s also a free spin bonus and randomly triggered jackpot that give the player something to chase after.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol.
The Scatter appears on reels two, three, and four. If the player hits seven or more Scatters on one spin, they win twice their bet and a free spin bonus.
Seven Scatters get the player seven free spins, eight gets them fourteen, nine gets them thirty.
The slot is also connected up with the EGT jackpot system which pools four progressive jackpots. Each pot is named for the suit of a card. When the jackpot is triggered (at random, at the end of a spin), the player is dealt twelve cards. They turn the cards over one at a time and the first suit they get three of is the jackpot they are awarded.
The higher the stakes the player is playing, the more likely the jackpot is to trigger. In this way, the RTP remains the same despite the difference in the ratio between varied bet sizes and absolute jackpot sizes.

media.caption: Stacked symbols can award a big enough win if player gets lucky

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.17%, a little over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.30 up to a maximum of $/£/€90.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a weak match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility. Sometimes a high RTP can make up for this, but Amazon’s Battle just isn’t high enough in either department.

media.caption: Full paytable for Amazon's Battle slot

Conclusion.text:
Players looking for a thrill might want to give this one a skip. The RTP isn’t bad, but the volatility just isn’t high enough to work with our preferred strategies.
For anyone making their own way, who isn’t too bothered by the volatility, this is a decent slot with a nice theme, some solid graphics, but rather short on atmosphere.
Overall, this is a good slot, but not one that we can recommend very highly.

20 Diamonds Review.text: 20 Diamonds is a video slot coming from EGT. This is quite a simple game with a fast gameplay and pretty much no bonus features. Still the slot has the potential for some big payouts thanks to stacked symbols on the reels and a rich paytable. If you like playing simple games 20 Diamonds is guaranteed to catch your attention.

media.caption: Stacked symbols offer some nice winnings, if you are lucky enough

Theme and Visual Details.text: For this slot the EGT designers decided to go with a Gems theme. The visual details of the slot are great, with modern animations and high symbol details. The designers also used bright colors to give the slot a luxury appearance.

Gameplay.text: The gameplay in 20 Diamonds is very fast and exciting. Since the game symbols land stacked across the reels players can easily land a few reels of matching symbols or even a full screen of identical symbols. This detail compensates for the fact that the slot lacks a classic bonus round.

media.caption: Gameplay video - there is nothing special in this slot beyond the Scatter and Wild symbols

Bet size and payouts.text:
20 Diamonds is a 20 payline slot with 5 reels and 3 rows. You can bet anywhere from $0.01 to $12 per spin and you can also adjust the number of pay lines from 1 to 20.
The top payout in the game is set at 500 times the total stake for landing 5 scatters anywhere on the screen. The game comes with an RTP value of 95.8% and with a low to medium variance.

media.caption: Paytable of 20 Diamonds slot is rather simple

Bonus features.text:
This is one of the few EGT slots which don’t have a classic bonus round. The Scatter symbol doesn’t trigger any bonus feature and only offers a payout of up to 500 times the total stake.
The Wild symbol in the game is the Seven and it can land stacked on all of the reels. The Wild symbol will replace all other symbols in the game except for the Scatter symbol.
20 Diamonds also comes with four jackpots attached. The jackpot game in the slot is triggered randomly. The player will need to make picks from 12 facedown cards on the screen. Once three cards are matched the corresponding jackpot is awarded.

media.caption: Scatter symbol is the top paying symbol of this slot

Conclusion.text: 20 Diamonds is a simple video slot which doesn’t have much to offer in terms of bonus features. The game has a low to medium variance and a rich paytable with stacked symbols on the reels. Thanks to this detail players can land some great payouts on the reels of 20 Diamonds.

title: Extra Stars
overview:
Extra Stars
    
        Play Extra Stars demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: With medium volatility and an RTP of 95.78%, this slot does have much extra of anything, let alone stars.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Following in the footsteps of many a fruit machine slot, Extra Stars sports melons and cherries and sevens. But it does so in a format that is poised between the minimalism of most fruit machines and the ordinary slot.
This falling between camps makes the theme feel a little off in some way.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are solid, but uninteresting.
The patterned background and the simple symbols look nice enough. But they are indistinguishable from a million other slots just like it.
Similarly, its animations and music are more or less the same as many other slots, especially those coming from EGT. On the whole, the front end design does little to distinguish it from its competition.

media.caption: Win in the Extra Stars slot

Gameplay.text:
Extra Stars has five reels and three rows. The ten win lines count in both directions and player can change between one, three, five, seven and ten win lines.
There is a gamble feature for anyone who fancies upping the rather paltry volatility of the game.
And for fans of bonus features, there is both a randomly triggered jackpot system and Wild respins, but no bonus features.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols. When a Wild lands, it expands to fill its reel and triggers a free respin with the Wilds locked in place.
Wilds only appear on reels 2, 3, and 4.
The jackpots can be triggered at the end of any regular spin. There are four of them, all progressive. Each is assigned the suit of a card.
When the jackpot is triggered, the player is dealt twelve cards. They turn the cards one by one until they have three matching suits. The jackpot which matches that suit is then awarded to the player.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 95.78%, a little under our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€20.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a poor match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Full paytable for Extra Stars slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Not simple enough to be a minimalist slot, not complex enough to feel like a full blown slot, Extra Stars is off to a rough start.
The low RTP and medium volatility make it terrible for using our slot strategies. That the slot offers very little to make up for it, is the reason we can dismiss this one so easily.
We do not recommend this slot in the slightest.

Egypt Sky review.text: Egypt Sky is a video slot coming from the EGT factory. This is a decent slot with a medium variance and the potential for some nice payouts. Even though it’s not one of the best slots coming from EGT it can still boost your balance a bit with some help from lady luck.

Theme and Visual Details.text:
As you can already guess this slot is inspired by Ancient Egypt. No Egyptian slot is complete without Queen Cleopatra on the reels and you can also see a variety of other symbols which follow the theme like the Pyramids, Scarab and Chariot symbols.
The visual details in the slot are decent and the designers went for a vintage appearance in Egypt Sky.

Gameplay.text: Like in most other EGT slots the gameplay in Egypt Sky is fast. What makes the gameplay exciting in this slot is the fact that the game symbols can land stacked across the reels. This way you can score some very nice payouts even without triggering the bonus round.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
Egypt Sky is a 40 payline slot with 5 reels and 4 rows of symbols.
Players can bet anywhere from $0.40 to $8 per spin. The slot has an RTP value of 96.3% and a medium variance.

media.caption: Full paytable in Egypt Sky

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol in Egypt Sky is the Ankh and it will substitute for all other symbols in the slot except for the Scatter Pyramid symbol.
The Wild can land only on reels 1, 2 and 3. Each time the Wild can contribute to a winning combination it will expand to cover the entire reel.
The Scatter symbol in Egypt Sky comes in the form of a Pyramid. In order to trigger the free spins bonus you will need to land 3, 4 or 5 Scatters anywhere on the reels. In return you are awarded 3, 5 or 7 free spins accordingly, which unfortunately can’t be re-triggered in any way.
During the free spins every Wild symbol which lands on the reels expands to cover the entire reel and stays in position until the feature ends. You can clearly see that in order to score a massive payout in the game you will need to trigger the bonus with the maximum number of scatters and land 3 wilds on the reels in the first few spins of the feature.

media.alt: Expanding symbol win in Egypt Sky
media.caption: Wild symbol expands when you could achieve a winning combination
Game rules of special features in Egypt Sky slot

Conclusion.text: Egypt Sky is a simple video slot which has decent visual details and a popular theme. But realistically the designers didn’t quite do a great job with the bonus feature. The number of free spins awarded in the feature is too low if you trigger the bonus with only 3 Scatters. You already know that it’s almost next to impossible to trigger a bonus round with the maximum 5 Scatters. This is why it’s going to be very hard to score a big payout in the bonus round and you will need a lot of luck to do that.

Theme and Storyline.text:
The palace at Versailles is one of the great architectural undertakings of the Early Modern period. During the 1600s it was expanded from a royal hunting lodge to the main residence of the King of France under Louis XIV. The Sun King, as he was known, was a symbol of royal excess and appears as the highest value symbol in this slot.
Also appearing are Cardinal Mazarin – a notable hanger-on of Louis’s – and a more generic busty courtesan, for the seduction of which Louis was infamous.
Playing on the reputation for opulence this slot takes you back in time.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are a bit kitsch, conveying less in the way of majestic royal wealth and more in the way of a first year graphic design student.
The accompanying sound and animations do very little to elevate this EGT slot game.
The sounds, for example, are not themed with a view to immersion, but are the standard spin and win sounds that EGT use on their most lazily skinned slots. While the animations are just flashing lines to indicate wins.

media.caption: Win in the Versailles Gold slot machine

The gameplay of Versailles Gold is similarly basic. The main appeal is that there are progressive jackpots. However, the base game is just a five by three slot with ten win lines.
There is a gamble feature in an attempt to provide variety, and that is useful for ramping up the volatility of the slot to better serve our slot strategies.
But on the whole, the gameplay doesn’t stray far from the absolute essentials.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Jackpot symbol.
The Wild symbol will also trigger the Free Spin bonus if three Wilds land anywhere on the reels during a single spin.
The Free Spin Bonus comes with twelve free spins and an Expanding Symbol. The Expanding Symbol is chosen at random from the regular symbols at the start of the Free Spins. For the remainder of the Free Spins, when that symbol lands on a reel it will expand to fill that reel immediately after the wins have been calculated. Any new winning combinations are then added to the total wins for that spin.
The Jackpot triggers randomly during the base game. If a jackpot is triggered, it occurs at the end of a spin. The player is then offered twelve cards face down and must select cards until they have three matching cards. The player then wins the jackpot that is featured on the matching cards.

media.caption: Randomly chosen Expanding Symbol fills the reel on which it lands

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.09%, very close to our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium-high, which makes it a moderately good match for our preferred slot machine strategies.

media.caption: Full paytable of the Versailles Gold slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Versailles Gold’s main appeal is that it pairs a decent RTP with a relatively high volatility, making it a good match with our preferred strategies.
Apart from that, it is a bit rough. The visuals feel as out of date as the French monarchy and the gameplay isn’t doing much of interest.
The main selling point is the jackpots, but there are plenty of other slots out there with a better base game offering the same thing.

title: Majestic Forest
overview:
Majestic Forest
    
        Play Majestic Forest demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Enter the majestic forest with wild animals, a mysterious dolmen, medium-high volatility and 96.19% RTP.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Majestic Forest has for its setting the woodlands of the northern United States. Bears, foxes and elk live in harmony. And at its heart a strange stone dolmen sits.
The ethereal green beauty of the background and symbols justify the makers giving the forest setting the adjective "majestic."
There are plenty of animal based slots out there, but few focus on this particular ecosystem. As a result, it feels fresh, and the forest is oddly relaxing. Come in under the leaves.

media.caption: Majestic Forest - win in the base game

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The front end of the slot is pretty good.
It still has some of the clunkiness of other EGT slots. For example, there is no background music and the win and spin sounds are generic. But the artwork is quality stuff and the background is really quite attractive.
The animations are simple, but work well with the artwork and the generally quite laid back feel of the slot.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Gameplay.text:
The gameplay is the standard EGT fare. A five reel slot with three rows and up to ten winlines. There is the usual four tier progressive jackpot system and a simple free spin bonus.
There is a gamble feature that allows players to play for double or nothing on a fifty-fifty shot. This doesn’t affect the RTP, but ramps up the volatility whenever it is used.

media.caption: Standard EGT gamble feature

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol is also the Scatter symbol and it substitutes for all other symbols.
Three or more Scatter symbols anywhere on the reels trigger the Free Spin Bonus. The player gets twelve free spins with a randomised expanding symbol. The expanding symbol expands to fill the reel whenever it lands during a spin.
It is a pretty simple bonus feature, but you can always use the gamble feature to spice things up.
There are four progressive jackpots, one for each of the suits in a deck of cards. They increase at different rates and so in general their size runs from clubs, diamonds, hearts, to spades.
A Jackpot Bonus can randomly trigger at the end of any base game spin. When the jackpot triggers, the player is taken to a picking game in which they are dealt 12 cards face down. The player then turns cards over until they hit three cards all in the same suit. The player is then awarded the jackpot of the same suit.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.19%, a little over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€60.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium to high, which makes it a match for our preferred slot machine strategies, but a very weak one. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Full paytable for Majestic Forest slot machine

Conclusion.text:
With nice visuals and decent gameplay, Majestic Forest is a good slot for fans of animal themed slots that are a bit more chilled out than they are wild.
With medium-high volatility and the long shot of bringing home one of the big jackpots, this game works quite well with our preferred slot strategies. The average RTP could be higher, but isn’t bad.
Overall, we recommend this slot.

title: Shining Crown
overview:
Shining Crown
    
        Play Shining Crown demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: A simple one-armed bandit style slot with a four-tiered jackpot system rather than a bonus game. It plays well with high volatility and an RTP of 96.37%.

Theme and Storyline.text:
The decorative theme for Shining Crown from EGT is that of a classic slot machine. The usual one-armed bandit symbols of lucky-7s, bells, cherries and other assorted fruit make an appearance coupled with the titular crowns for a Wild symbol.
It is a time honoured design and works as well as any of the numerous similar games cashing on on the caché of old school designs.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are lovely, high def symbols roll around well animated reels.
The sound design is in keeping with the theme – i.e. very basic. There is no music and the soundtrack is largely a kind of mechanical whirr when you spin the reels and a pleasing thunk when they stop.
Unfortunately, it is all a very glossy version of a type of slot we’ve seen hundreds of times before. That said, it does its version extremely competently.

Gameplay.text:
The gameplay is extremely simple. In the absence of Bonus symbols the main deviation from the usual "push button, lose or win money, rinse, repeat" style play is the jackpots (see below).
There is also a red/black gamble option just in case you want to up your variance in what is already a pretty high-variance game, but even this feels very bog-standard when compared to all the other games out there.

media.caption: Shining crown slot has a gamble function
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
Rather than the usual bonuses triggered by hitting a combo of symbols, Shining Crown offers instead a kind of hybrid bonus and jackpot system. They call this the Mystery Jackpot.
There are four jackpots – one per suit. These take a small contribution from each bet made per spin by all players of the game and are constantly building up at the top of the screen you play in. Every now and again random spins get awarded the jackpot.
If you are lucky enough to be rewarded one, then a new bonus game opens up. The bonus game is made up of twelve face-down cards (three of each suit). You turn over the cards until you reveal three of the same suit. You are then rewarded half the amount of the jackpot you won.
The jackpots grow at different rates so usually, the Clubs are the smallest and Spades the largest, though as in the image below where the diamond jackpot was recently hit, your mileage may vary.
In addition to this bonus game, Shining Crown has a Wild symbol with a crown on it. This plays as any symbol but the two Scatter symbols. It also expands to cover the whole reel if it helps you to form a winning line.
One of the scatters is a Standard Scatter. Hit any three, four or five of this symbol to win 5, 20 or 100 times your bet per spin respectively.
The other is a Special Scatter (star symbol) you have to hit three of these on the only three reels it appears in order to win a prize of 20 times your bet per spin.

media.caption: Shining Crown offers a chance to win one of 4 Jackpots

media.alt: Big win with expanding wild symbols
media.caption: With enough luck you can hit big win with 2 expanding wild symbols in Shining Crown slot

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The RTP of 96.37% is around the rough average for the industry and with a range of 10 to 600 coins per spin, you can get a decent range sizes for your bet per spin by altering the value of the coins.
Symbols are often stacked so hitting combos is rarer, but do tend to be fairly large when you do hit a winning combo (or rather "winning combos"). The result is that playing Shining Crown can result in highly-volatile results for your bankroll. You’ll want to come to the table with enough cash to ride out the long gaps between wins.

media.caption: Full paytable of the Shining Crown slot

Conclusion.text:
Shining Crown is a pretty simplistic game to be sure, but the high volatility and average RTP mean that it plays pretty well with some of our favoured strategies.
Apart from that, the visuals are decent. In fact, the main disadvantage of the game is that the bonus game isn’t terribly exciting to play most of the other features are pretty solid.

about_game: An RTP of 95.74% and a lack of bonus features are the only real downsides to this minimalist slot from EGT.

Theme and Storyline.text:
EGT seem pretty happy with their fruit machine formula. There are a load of slots in their Hot range, all united by the fruit machine symbols, orange colour scheme, and – in many cases – a shared jackpot pool.
The theme overall is fairly malleable and EGT apply it to many of their games. Here it is a five win line, three by five slot, while elsewhere there are more complex versions, and an even simpler three by three version.
As themes go, therefore, it has demonstrated robustness. If robustness is your thing, this could be the slot for you.

media.caption: Win in the 5 Dazzling Hot slot

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
EGT have this down to a fine art at this point. The images are simple, easily read, and look good on their dark orange backgrounds.
The reels are well animated, with simple clear animations, and they look good on their light orange background.
There is no music, but the sound effects are also clear and simple and work well with the simple gameplay and design.

Gameplay.text:
The gameplay elements of 5 Dazzling Hot are more or less what you’d expect from any run of the mill modern slot. There are five reels, three rows, and five win lines.
To spice things up there is a gamble feature. The main thing that is missing from a slot like this is some kind of bonus. 5 Dazzling Hot just has a randomly triggered jackpot instead (see below for details).
So, overall, the gameplay is neither a selling point nor a detraction from this slot. In fact, the gameplay is more or less invisible.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There is no Wild symbol and no bonuses or free spins in 5 Dazzling Hot.
However, at the end of any spin the player can win a jackpot. This is randomised, but the higher the stakes the player is using, the better their chance of triggering the jackpot.
If the player is lucky enough to have triggered a jackpot, then they are offered a chance at a picking game. The player is dealt twelve cards, each of which has the name of a jackpot on the back. The player then picks cards from those twelve cards until they reveal three cards with the same jackpot on them. The player then wins that jackpot.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 95.74%, a good quarter of a percentage point below our rough yardstick for average of around 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.05 up to a maximum of $/£/€50.00 per spin. This is a much lower minimum than many slots and may appeal to micro stakes gamers.
The volatility of this game, like many of the Hot games, is high. This makes for an excellent match with our preferred slot machine strategies, which target the highest possible volatility in the slots we chose.

media.caption: Paytable for 5 Dazzling Hot slot machine

Conclusion.text:
5 Dazzling Hot is a decent slot, simple and efficient.
The low RTP is a big stumbling block for us. One which is only partially made up for by the high volatility and the jackpot feature.
Players do need to be happy with very stripped down gameplay to get much out of this one though. But if that is your bag, we might give this slot a light recommendation.

title: Witches' Charm
overview:

about_game: Allow yourself to be beguiled by the seductive Witches’ Charm and its medium-high volatility with an RTP of 95.97%.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Witches’ Charm is a punny title, playing both on the idea of witches magical powers – which include charms along with hexes, curses and spells – and on how charmingly sexy the witches in this slot are.
EGT are leaning heavily on the sexy witch motif here and use it to create a magical world of cauldrons and crystal balls. They appear on the reels as symbols along with the classic familiars: an owl and a black cat.
The setting is a woodland where anything could happen and the glimmer in the trees is as likely to be fairies as glow worms.

media.caption: Base game win

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The game’s setting is beautifully rendered with detailed artwork in the style of a fantasy novel’s cover illustrations. Each symbol has its own illustration which kicks into gear when it becomes part of a winning combo.
The game does not have much in the way of music, relying for its sound almost entirely on spin and win sounds. Though these sound effects do work and lend the game a much-needed atmosphere, and the win sound is almost a musical soundtrack all by itself.

Gameplay.text:
The gameplay is that of a five reel, three row slot, with fifteen win lines.
Any winnings a player makes on a spin can be gambled in a double or nothing game of Red or Black.
There are also a free spin bonus and a jackpot feature, both of which are explained in full below. Sufficed to say, this covers the key things one might hope for from a standard 21st century slot.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol. Wins including a Wild are doubled. If it lands two or more on a winline running left to right from reel one, it also pays out as the highest value symbol, far more valuable than any regular symbol.
Two Scatter symbols anywhere on the reels pays out double the player’s bet per spin. Three or more increases the payout and also awards the player fifteen free spins. During the free spins, any winning combinations receive a x3 multiplier. The free spins can be retriggered.
There are also four progressive jackpots. The Jackpot Feature is triggered at random at the end of a spin. When triggered, the Jackpot Feature begins with a picking game.
Twelve cards are dealt out face down, with each card having the name of one of the four progressive jackpots on it. The player picks cards until they have three matching cards, and the jackpot whose symbol appears on the three matching cards is then awarded to the player.

media.caption: Standard EGT gamble function

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 95.97%. This is more or less what we consider average. We use a rough yardstick of around 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.15 up to a maximum of $/£/€90.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is in the murky grey area between medium and high, which makes it a decent match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Paytable for Witches' Charm slot

Conclusion.text:
The charms of Witches’ Charm are bewitching enough to keep people playing it. The slot enjoys a moderate, but consistent popularity with the punters. And one can see why.
Everything about the game is competently designed and executed. The gameplay is well paced and various enough to keep players interested, while the visuals and sounds project a unified sense of atmosphere.
The medium-high volatility makes this a good slot to use with our preferred strategies and the average RTP should work for most players.
We give this one a strong recommendation.

There are no gamble features or varied bonuses to spice things up and the central game mechanics are all pretty basic. This is not necessarily a bad thing but will depend on the taste of the player.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Free Spin and Golden Seven symbol.
The Free Spin symbol appears only on reels one, three and five. If the player lands a Free Spin symbol on all three reels, a Free Spin Bonus is triggered with eight free spins.
The Free Spin Bonus can be retriggered by hitting another three Free Spin symbols with no upper limit to the total number of spins the player can win. During the Free Spin Bonus, there are more Wild symbols on the reels, making for more chances at bigger, multi-way wins.
The Golden Seven symbol (which looks like the regular Seven symbol but with a cluster of diamonds at its base) triggers the Jackpot Bonus. The Jackpot Bonus is a picking game. The player is presented with twelve diamonds, under each of which is a symbol indicating either the mini, minor, major or mega jackpot. The player picks diamonds until they hit three of the same symbol. They then win the corresponding amount.
The jackpots are fixed multiples of the player’s bet per spin. The mini jackpot is ten times the player's bet per spin, while the mega jackpot – the biggest – is worth 1,000 times the player's bet per spin.

media.caption: More Wild symbols appear during the Free Spin Bonus
The Jackpot Bonus is a picking game

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.48%, comfortably over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.15 up to a maximum of $/£/€75.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a weak match for our preferred slot machine strategies, which tend to favour high volatility.

media.caption: Full paytable of the Diamond Strike slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Diamond Strike is a pretty decent slot. What it lacks in imagination, it makes up for in solidity.
The main appeal is the jackpot system that allows players to win as much as 1,000 times their bet per spin in one go, but overall the volatility is not that high. Jackpot games normally appeal due to the high volatility and the opportunity for life-changing wins which that represents.
Overall, Diamond Strike doesn’t quite make the cut and fails to win our recommendation.

title: Wolf Gold
overview:
Wolf Gold
    
        Play Wolf Gold demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: You can run with the pack in Wolf Gold, out onto the plains. The gameplay is pretty good and the RTP is about what we’d expect. Its RTP of 96% is nothing to write home about and we’d like much higher variance on this slot. With those caveats in place, we can make a slight recommendation for this slot.

Theme and Storyline.text:
The plains of North America are host to a vast ecosystem of beautiful and majestic creatures. This is a fact that slot machines cannot resist and so Wolf Gold joins a regular pantheon of slots with buffalo, cougar, and bald eagle bedecked slot machines.
This one focuses on the wolf pack with its stacked wilds with the face of a wolf painted onto them.
In the background is the red sandstone of Monument Valley and in the foreground, the symbols are all laid over reels the colour of desert sand.

media.caption: Attractive visuals of the Wolf Gold slot

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are nicely painted in the very particular style of American Mural art that looks both difficult, detailed and kind of cheap. But despite this, the aesthetic is well in keeping with the theme and with the exception of the ace to jack symbols the visual style works.
This is coupled with simple but effective animations and a soundtrack of wolves howling and the wind blowing that really creates an atmosphere.
Overall the design elements of this slot from Pragmatic Play work surprisingly well.

Gameplay.text:
The gameplay is pretty good, with several fun twists to keep an eye on. There are the stacked Wilds which make for some exciting moments when a big win almost appears thanks to multiple winlines catching a couple of consecutive stacks of Wilds.
This is coupled with the Money symbol bonuses (more on this below) and the attendant three jackpots of differing sizes.
Overall there is a lot to like in Wolf Gold that makes the gameplay more than just a simple twenty-five win line slot machine.

media.caption: Wild symbols are stacked on reels in Wolf Gold slot
Gameplay video with Money symbols respin feature

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol plays as any symbol except for the Money bonus or the Scatter. The Wilds are stacked.
The Scatter symbol appears only on reels one, three and five. If you hit three symbols you win an amount equal to your bet per spin and then play the Free Spin bonus. In the Free Spin round you receive five free spins and can retrigger three more spins by hitting three scatter symbols again. There is no limit to how many times you can retrigger the Free Spin bonus.
During your free spins the middle three reels are turned into one giant symbol which plays as if those three reels all landed on the same symbol. As a result all your wins will contain four or five symbols making for much bigger payouts.
The Money Bonus is triggered when six or more money symbols fall. These symbols are locked in place and the rest of the reels are spun again. During the Money Bonus every reel contains only Money symbols and blanks. You have three spins which reset every time you hit a money symbol. The game plays until you fill all the reels or your spins run out. You are then paid the amount on all the Money symbols added together. If you fill the reel you also win the maximum jackpot.

media.caption: Money symbols respin feature

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
This game has medium volatility and an RTP of 96.00%. So be aware that it is at the bottom of our recommended range.
The bet range per spin on the sites we tested were £/$/€0.25 to £/$/€125.00.

media.caption: Paytable of the Wolf Gold slot

Conclusion.text:
Wolf Gold is a fun slot with some cool bonus features that really elevate the gameplay from being just another prairie home companion slot machine.
Its main detraction is the medium volatility, but if you’re not going with our strategies you might opt to give this one a go.

overview:

about_game: This slot might look familiar to fans of Disney’s Aladdin, but the sense of style is only skin deep. Below the surface this is a very simple slot with an RTP of 96.53%.

Theme and Storyline.text:
In the long list of things that Disney are responsible for completely upending, the story of Aladdin is right up near the top. This slot, for example, although making no direct effort to come in as a cheap post-Disney knock-off, takes its imagery wholesale from the Mouse.
Ignoring the story’s original Chinese setting, and making particular use of the parrot and monkey characters from the cartoon, this slot falls squarely into the area of plagiarism. The genie is even blue.
In short, if you want your adult gambling to invoke your childhood cartoons, here’s a slot you might like.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
3 Genie Wishes has an excellent style. The "stolen" character designs are given a realism-makeover, rendering them closer to someone who might exist in the real world.
The music is a throbbing pseudo-Arabian track that drives the action forward excitingly and the win and spin sounds are low-key but effective.
The animations are rather dull for a slot which is trying so hard to be an animated film. Each symbol has a small win animation, but they are simple and perfunctory at best.
Overall, the slot has a superficially attractive style, though its simplicity may tire players who came for a sense of some whole new world-building.

media.caption: Epic win in the 3 Genie Wishes slot

Gameplay.text:
3 Genie Wishes is a five reel slot with four rows and fifty paylines.
There is no gamble feature, nor is there much in the way of other bells and whistles. The bonus game is a simple Free Spins style game.
Overall, the gameplay is rather less exotic than a slot built around a Robin Williams film should be.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol.
Three or more Scatter symbols anywhere on the reels trigger the Bonus Feature. This starts with a picking game, in which the player is awarded one of several Bonus Features based on what they pick.
The possible bonuses are:

media.caption: The Bonus Feature starts with a picking game
Raining Wilds randomly appear in one of the two versions of Free Spins

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.53%, nicely over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.50 up to a maximum of $/£/€250.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a relatively weak match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility in slots, some allowance is made for higher RTPs so this isn’t completely useless to players who are using these strategies.

media.caption: Full paytable of the 3 Genie Wishes slot machine

Conclusion.text:
3 Genie Wishes is a solid slot. It looks nice, has a recognisable theme, and a great soundtrack.
The gameplay is a bit basic, but it does rub the lamp in all the right places. And most players will be satisfied with a free spin bonus. Just don’t expect miracles from this genie.
The medium volatility is a bit of a drag, but coupled with a decent RTP doesn’t rule this one out at all.

title: 40 Burning Hot
overview:
40 Burning Hot
    
        Play 40 Burning Hot demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: 40 Burning Hot is a perfectly serviceable if rather bland slot with an RTP of 95.93% and medium volatility.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Some slot themes have become successful in ways that are hard to explain. The Hot series from EGT, for example, are all united by a similar visual style and a general use of fruit machine iconography. Some, like 40 Burning Hot, use the EGT progressive jackpot system, some don’t. Almost all of them use an orange colour scheme.
40 Burning Hot marks itself out as different with a mildly Irish twist on the formula: a green background is the biggest difference, but the four leafed clovers on the reels are also new.
This slot should work for most people who like a pretty straightforward theme, and aren’t looking for world building or story with their gambling kicks.

media.caption: Win in the 40 Burning Hot slot

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are a little clunky. They use the EGT software and borrow artwork from other games in the Hot series.
The animations are simple and straightforward. They do the job of keeping the gameplay outcomes clear to the player, but don’t add much in the way of style or atmosphere.
There is no music to go with all this. Just the basic spin and win sounds.

40 Burning Hot Gameplay.text:
The gameplay is pretty straightforward, the forty win lines of the title span a grid of five reels with four rows each.
There is a gamble feature that allows players to play double or nothing by guessing what colour the next card off a digital deck will be.
The main reason to play is that it gives the player a shot at the jackpot system (details below).

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins in 40 Burn.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Dollar and Star symbols.
The Dollar and Star symbols are Scatter symbols that pay out for three or more symbols anywhere on the reels.
The Dollar symbol appears on all reels and pays out three times the player’s total bet for three symbols, twenty times for four symbols, and one hundred times for five.
The Star symbol only appears on reels one, three and five and pays out twenty times the total bet for landing one on each of those three reels.
There are four progressive jackpots.
The Jackpot Feature may trigger the end of any random spin. When triggered, the Jackpot Feature begins with the player being offered a picking game with twelve cards. Each card has the name of one of the four progressive jackpots on the back. The player picks cards until three of the same jackpots are named.
The jackpot whose symbol appears on the three matching cards is then awarded to the player.

media.caption: Standard EGT's gambling feature

40 Burning Hot Bet Sizes, RTP and Varian.text:
The return to player of this game is 95.93%, barely under our rough yardstick for average of about 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.40 up to a maximum of $/£/€80.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium. Our preferred slot strategies use high volatility, so this slot is only a weak match for those. However, players who prefer lower volatility may find this to be a plus in a way that we don’t.

media.caption: Paytable for 40 Burning Hot slot

Conclusion.text:
Overall 40 Burning Hot doesn’t do much of anything new and fails to distinguish itself from the many other Hot games in the EGT stable. Though if you like those games, it means you will almost certainly like this one.
The gameplay is solid but uninspired, which is also true of just about everything about this slot, from the visuals to the RTP.

30 Spicy Fruits Review.text: 30 Spicy Fruits is a video slot coming from EGT. The slot has a simple design with stacked symbols and a free spins bonus round where players can score up to 30 free spins. Playing the slot can be a real enjoyment thanks to the frequent wins on the screen and the potential for bigger payouts in the bonus round. Like in most other EGT slots players have a chance to score one of the four attached jackpots.

Theme and Visual Details.text: As you can already guess from the slot name 30 Spicy Fruits comes with a fruit theme. The game also has a classic tone thanks to the Bars and Sevens symbols, while the spiciness comes from the Red Hot Chili Wild symbol. The symbols in the slot are well designed, with a few modern animations added to make it appealing to the eye.

media.caption: It's easy to hit multiple winlines with stacked symbols

Gameplay.text:
One detail which is common to all EGT slots is the fast gameplay. What makes the gameplay interesting in 30 Spicy Fruits are the stacked symbols. Thanks to this players can score a full screen of matching symbols and without a doubt a big payout.
If you like to spice up your gameplay, you can raise the volatility with the standard gamble function.

media.caption: Gameplay video featuring free spins bonus game

Bet size, RTP and variance.text:
30 Spicy Fruits is a fixed 30 payline slot, so the bet size can range anywhere from $0.30 up to $150 per spin.
The top payout combination comes from the Wild symbol, awarding a payout of 33 times the total stake for landing 5 of them on a winning payline. But players have a chance to land a full screen of Wilds with a top payout of 990 times the total stake in a single spin.
The slot comes with an RTP value of 95% and a medium to high variance, which could be well combined with our preferred strategies.

media.caption: Full paytable of 30 Spicy Fruits slot

Bonus features.text:
Like we mentioned earlier, all of the game symbols can land stacked across the reels. This includes the Wild and Scatter symbols, which can result in a full screen of Wilds and a big payout.
The Scatter symbol can land as a stacked symbol only on reels 2, 3 and 4. You will need to land 7, 8 or 9 Scatters on these central reels in order to trigger the free spins bonus. The player will get 7, 15 or 30 free spins accordingly which can be re-triggered on any spin, providing that another set of 7 or more scatters hit the reels.
The jackpot game in 30 Spicy Fruits can be triggered randomly on any given spin. When this happens the player will need to choose from 12 cards on the screen and match 3 of them. The card suit which is matched corresponds to one of the four jackpots.

media.caption: Slightly different take on scatter symbol in 30 Spicy Fruits slot - stacked on all 3 reels

Conclusion.text:
30 Spicy Fruits is a simple but attractive video slot coming from the EGT portfolio, offering higher than average variance. We could recommend this slot, if the RTP was little bit higher.
With its modern 30 payline design and attractive free spins bonus 30 Spicy Fruits can award payouts of up to 990 times the total stake per spin. If that’s not enough, with some luck on your side, you can trigger the jackpot game and win one of the four attached jackpots.

title: Koi Gate
overview:
Koi Gate
    
        Play Koi Gate demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: This high RTP (96.6%), medium volatility slot is an entrancing Japanese fantasy.

Theme and Storyline.text:
This slot is themed around a Japanese koi pond.
Players collect delicate waterlilies and ferocious dragons as wise-looking koi fish watch.
Set against rippling turquoise water, this game has a peaceful mood.

media.caption: Dragon Wild symbol win

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The gentle soundtrack has a traditional Japanese vibe filled with melodic flutes. It remains unobtrusive and players will likely be happy to leave it on for their gameplay.
The reels are framed by ornate Japanese lattices. This helps create the feeling that players are in an exquisitely kept garden.
Two hosting koi swim majestically on either side of the reels. Their bright orange colour contrasts with the azure water making the splash of their bodies more impressive.
Most symbols represent an aspect of nature, for example leaves, waves, waterlilies and bamboo. The dragon and koi symbols stand out as regal and especially well-designed.
Wild wins prompt the duel animation of a swimming koi and a flying dragon. This gives a mythical vibe to the reels.
When players begin the Re-Spins feature, the backdrop goes through a trippy transformation to become a dragon-filled sky. This furthers the feeling that there are some magical mysteries to the idyllic setting.

media.alt: Koi Gate slot expanded Wild symbol win
media.caption: Koi Wild symbol expands before wins are calculated

Gameplay.text:
Koi Gate is a five reel, three row slot, with 18 win lines.
Win lines pay in both directions starting from either reel 1 or 5. Players winning with five symbols on one winline are paid for the line both from right to left and left to right (effectively doubling their win).
Players have the option to hit stop on the spinning reel to speed up gameplay.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins in Koi Gat.text:
This slot has two Wild symbols (the Koi symbol and the dragon symbol). Each one substitutes for all symbols.
The Koi symbol appears only on reels 2, 3, and 4. When any Koi symbol is part of a winning combination, it expands into the dragon symbol to cover all positions before the winnings are awarded.
Players are awarded Re-Spins when one or more Koi symbols appear. Players win additional Re-Spins when one or more Koi symbols appear on screen while in the Re-Spins round.
There is no cap on Re-Spins and they continue to be awarded until a spin occurs in which no Koi symbol lands.
Players’ prizes are doubled while in the Re-Spins feature, and Re-Spins will be played according to the lines and bet of the game that triggered the feature.
The Progressive Jackpot Feature means that players may win the Progressive Jackpot at the end of any game round. This win is added to the players’ other wins.

Koi Gate Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.6%, above our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.18 up to a maximum of $/£/€900 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a less ideal match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.alt: Koi Gate slot top paying symbols paytable
media.caption: Paytable for high paying symbols of the game

Conclusion.text:
We recommend this high RTP, medium volatility Koi-themed slot.
This game makes up for its less desirable volatility by being a really pleasant place to hang out.
The animation and music work together to make the atmosphere feel mesmeric and fun.
Players looking for a lot of rough-and-tumble action may wish to look elsewhere, but for those looking for a dreamy escape, this game is just the ticket.

title: Gold Rush (Habanero)
overview:
Gold Rush (Habanero)
    
        Play Gold Rush (Habanero) demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Hee-haw, pardner! Head out west prospecting in this fantastic slot from Habanero. Set in the California Gold Rush hunt for gold nuggets and dodge bandits while chasing the impressive 98.1% return on this slot.

Theme and Storyline.text:
The California Gold Rush ran from the late 1840s to about 1855, a period of time in which thousands made their way into the wildernesses of California in search of gold in "them there hills". Naturally, that prospective hunt for gold in the cruel and luck driven world of the Wild West makes an excellent setting for a slot machine.
The iconography of the old West is a nice and easy one for any designer looking for an easily recognised theme. And the California gold rush, in particular, is a perfect fit for a slot machine where players speculate in their own hunt for riches.
Habanero’s Gold Rush slot game plays on this theme to full effect with plenty of old timers, pack mules, dynamite and gold nuggets sprinkling the screen.

media.caption: Good quality in reel spin animation

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Gold Rush really excels in this area. The reels are beautifully designed with easy to recognise graphics and plenty of character.
These are all animated smoothly and with great flashiness when the reel spins and when a symbol is part of a winning combination in particular. Even the background is perfectly suited to the atmosphere of the game.
All of this is set to a quality low-key sound design which couples both music and ambient sound to make for an immersive playing atmosphere.

Gameplay.text:
The game works on a standard five-reel system with three symbols per reel and 25 win lines, of which you must play all 25.
There is also a randomised progressive jackpot which can be won on any spin.
The game has a nice selection of fun bonus features (see below for details) and although the gameplay isn’t anything special, it does well what it sets out to do.

media.caption: Big win thanks to the progressive jackpot hit
Gameplay video featuring one of the bonuses

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There are the usual special symbols on Gold Rush: Wilds and Bonuses.
A golden nugget signified the Wild (aka "Substitute") symbol which plays as any symbol except a bonus and if you get three or more on a win line is also the most valuable regular symbol.
The dynamite symbol serves as both a Scatter and Bonus symbol. Hit three or more and you win a multiple of your bet per spin and trigger 10, 12 or 15 free spins depending on whether you hit three, four or five symbols respectively.
During the free spins, there is a Mine Collapse feature which can happen at random. When it does 3-15 of the same symbol will fall at random into the slots on your reels.
These bonus games are, as with most games, the big winners.

media.caption: Rules of the bonus games

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The game has low-volatility that may deter the more gamble happy of players, but with a return to player of 98.1% this slot machine is extremely tempting.
How much this appeals to you will depend on your bankroll and the reasons for playing. Bankroll in particular is important for this slot as with no ability to change the number of lines you play your only control over your bet per spin is coin size and number of coins per spin.

media.caption: Full paytable

Conclusion.text:
Gold Rush is a fun, well-designed game with great graphics and a high RTP.
Its main downside is the simple bonus games and – for those who play our strategies – the low-volatility.
On the whole, it is easy to recommend as a gambling experience.

title: Zeus
overview:
Zeus
    
        Play Zeus demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Ancient Greece and its God of Thunder might seem exciting, but this drab slot machine fails to entice with design, gameplay, or its statistics. We’re not angry, just disappointed.

Theme and Storyline.text:
The mightiest God on Olympus was Zeus, King of the Gods and Lord of Thunder. Mythology, with its recognisable iconography, always makes for a good slot theme.
That is what Habanero’s Zeus slot works with. Here, Zeus is accompanied by his wife Hera, and a range of generic Ancient Greek artefacts – shields, busts, and pottery for the most part though with plenty of Ace to Ten symbols written in a pseudo-greek angular script.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics and animations are certainly solid. The animations are smooth and slick.
Unfortunately, the actual designs for the slot do not match up to the technical competence. The pictures are bland and uninteresting. The whole slot lacks much sense of character, that can make other slots from Habanero so engaging.
The sound effects make no effort to be in keeping with the theme and are more or less bog-standard slot machine noises.

media.alt: Zeus slot 5 of a kind win
media.caption: Example of 5 of a kind win in Habanero's slot Zeus

Gameplay.text:
The main game is a typical 5x3 slot machine, with 1, 3, 5, 10, 15, 20 or 25 win-lines as per your choice as a player.
Beyond that, the game has a free spin bonus and almost no other features.
As a result, the gameplay is not the most engaging. This would be forgivable in a slot that had a little more charm.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The game has just two special symbols.
There is a Wild symbol on which is painted the titular Zeus. It plays as a typical wild symbol substituting for all symbols except the Scatter symbol. When you hit a winning combo with him he animates in a drab way.
The main perk of the Wild symbol is that if you hit a win-line with multiple Wild symbols, the payout can be huge – 15 times your bet per line for two, 150 for three, 1500 for four and a whopping 15,000 for five on one win-line.
The other symbol is a Scatter symbol which pays out whenever you hit two or more. The payouts for this are rather lower than the wild (hit five and you win just 200 times your bet, hit four and you win just 5 times your bet).
If you hit three or more Scatter symbols you also trigger the free spins. This is where the big wins are made. You win 5, 15 or 50 spins depending on if you get three, four or five scatters. Although you cannot retrigger the feature, every time you hit a scatter during the free spins you gain +1 free spin.
During the free spins, all the payouts are also tripled.
There is also a jackpot feature which triggers at random. 0.45% of each bet is split between three differently sized jackpots. The more you contribute to a jackpot the better your odds of triggering it.

media.caption: Explanation of bonus game rules in Zeus slot
Balance rises considerably when you catch a progressive jackpot win in Zeus slot from Habanero

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The RTP of the game is just 96.03%, this is very vanilla, and more or less what you would expect of something that is so average it hurts.
The variance is also pretty mid-range. Though this can be adjusted by playing a different number of lines with the same total bet.
Which is good, because bet controls allow you to tailor all that very easily. You can almost bet any amount between the maximum of £/€/$250.00 per spin and minimum of £/€/$0.01 per spin.

media.caption: Paytable of Habanero's Zeus slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Habanero’s Zeus slot machine is a thoroughly undistinctive and unremarkable slot.
Very little stands out about it from the beige design, copy-pasted artworks and the lack of soundtrack.
Even the volatility and RTP are middle of the road. We would not recommend this slot to anyone who is trying to stay awake while they play.
